<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title><![CDATA[WSJ - EN-US - world]]></title><link/> https://www.wsj.com/news/world <atom:link href="https://rsshub.app/wsj/en-us/world" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><description><![CDATA[WSJ - EN-US - world - Made with love by RSSHub(https://github.com/DIYgod/RSSHub)]]></description><generator> RS集线器</generator><webmaster>i@diygod.me (DIYgod)</webmaster><language> zh-cn</language><lastbuilddate> 2023 年 7 月 21 日星期五 18:03:14 GMT</lastbuilddate><ttl> 120 </ttl><item><title><![CDATA[U.S. to Send More Warships, Marines to Middle East Amid Rising Tensions With Iran]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>过去三个月，华盛顿向该地区派遣了部队，阻止伊朗军队针对商船<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001072734"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="688" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-821405?width=860&amp;height=688" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">监控视频拍摄的图像显示，上个月，三艘伊朗船只靠近霍尔木兹海峡的一艘商船。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：美国海军/美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001072734"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/dion-nissenbaum" itemprop="url" rel="author">迪昂·尼森鲍姆</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 7 月 21 日中午 12:22（东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-sending-more-warships-marines-to-middle-east-amid-rising-tensions-with-iran-dfc3a048"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>美国军方表示，正在向中东派遣更多军舰和海军陆战队员，以阻止伊朗在该地区扣押更多船只。</p><p>五角大楼周四晚间表示，在美国海军挫败了<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/iran-tried-to-seize-two-oil-tankers-near-strait-of-hormuz-u-s-navy-says-4be301e1?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">伊朗本月早些时候在阿曼湾国际水域扣押两艘油轮的企图</a>后，国防部长劳埃德·奥斯汀下令向该地区增派新部队。一名美国军方官员表示，此举并不是针对特定的新威胁，而是针对伊朗的行动。</p><p>中东盟友一直敦促美国采取更多措施对抗伊朗，伊朗在今年春天的一周内扣押了两艘油轮，其中一艘将科威特原油运往休斯敦，供<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/CVX" class="">雪佛龙</a>公司使用<span class="company-name-type">。</span></p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-pressured-to-secure-persian-gulf-after-iran-seizes-tankers-7bab70cb?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">阿拉伯联合酋长国对美国对今年早些时候伊朗扣押油轮事件缺乏回应表示特别失望</a>，并呼吁五角大楼向波斯湾派遣更多部队。</p><p>过去三个月，美国向中东派遣了一系列部队，阻止伊朗军队干扰通过该地区的商船。</p><p> 4月初，在伊朗扣押两艘油轮之前，美国<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-sends-submarine-to-middle-east-in-show-of-force-441dbb42?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">派出一艘导弹潜艇</a>进入红海。扣押事件发生后，美国向该地区派遣了一艘导弹驱逐舰，并使用侦察机密切监视阿曼湾一艘油轮周围的伊朗海军活动。</p><p>即使有新的动向，美国在中东的军事存在仍将远远小于伊拉克和阿富汗战争期间部署的兵力，因为五角大楼近年来一直寻求将战略重点转向中国和俄罗斯。但伊朗的行动，包括最近对波斯湾航运的威胁，促使五角大楼将部队转移回中东。</p><p>此外，俄罗斯喷气式战斗机加大了对叙利亚上空美国飞机的骚扰力度，美国官员表示，这似乎是莫斯科向美国施压，迫使其从该地区撤军。美国官员表示，伊朗人也有同样的目标。</p><p>负责监督美国在叙利亚以及中东和东南亚其他 20 个国家上空的军事行动的空军中将亚历克苏斯·格林克维奇 (Alexus Grynkewich) 上个月表示，“伊朗人当然希望联军撤离叙利亚，这样他们就可以有行动自由，让与伊朗结盟的团体为了自己的目的而在叙利亚各地运送先进的常规武器和致命能力。”</p><p>迄今为止，美国威慑伊朗的努力收效有限。</p><p>本月早些时候，美国海军挫败了伊朗军队两次分别扣押两艘商业油轮的企图。海军表示，第二天，伊朗军队确实扣押了第三艘涉嫌走私石油的商船。对于这种情况，美国海军表示没有干预。</p><p>美国现在正在采取更多措施来对抗伊朗。本周早些时候， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-deploys-advanced-f-35-jets-destroyer-to-middle-east-to-brush-back-iranian-forces-7d9a92cf?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">五角大楼表示将向该地区派遣最先进的喷气式战斗机</a>——F-35。现在，五角大楼正在派遣一个海军陆战队两栖战备小组和海军陆战队远征部队，其中至少有两艘舰艇和最多 2,500 名海军陆战队员。</p><p>美国中央司令部司令、陆军上将埃里克·库里拉表示，新部队将有助于“保障国际商业的自由流动……维护基于规则的国际秩序，并阻止伊朗在该地区破坏稳定的活动。”</p><p>美国军方表示，过去两年，伊朗已针对该地区近20艘商船进行攻击。</p><p>美国对抗伊朗的努力超出了波斯湾。今年三月，五角大楼<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-strikes-iranian-backed-group-in-syria-after-drone-attack-kills-one-american-and-wounds-six-9f3dafe6?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">针对叙利亚境内伊朗支持的武装分子进行了空袭</a>，以应对无人机袭击叙利亚境内美国基地并造成一名美国承包商死亡的事件。</p><p>美国官员表示，美国的袭击迫使伊朗缩减了针对该地区美军的企图。但伊朗反而加大了针对波斯湾商船的攻击力度，全球超过三分之一的海运原油都在此过境。</p><p>写信给迪昂·尼森鲍姆 (Dion Nissenbaum)： <a href="mailto:dion.nissenbaum@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">dion.nissenbaum@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 21 Jul 2023 16:22:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/us-sending-more-warships-marines-to-middle-east-amid-rising-tensions-with-iran-dfc3a048</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/us-sending-more-warships-marines-to-middle-east-amid-rising-tensions-with-iran-dfc3a048<author><![CDATA[Dion Nissenbaum]]></author><category>活力</category><category>军用船只</category><category>航空航天/国防</category><category>国防设备/产品</category><category>化石燃料</category><category>工业品</category><category>油和气</category><category>油</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>武装部队</category><category>海军</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>武装部队</category><category>海军</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>军事行动</category><category>活力</category><category>军用船只</category><category>航天</category><category>防御</category><category>国防装备</category><category>产品</category><category>化石燃料</category><category>工业品</category><category>油和气</category><category>油</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Sergey Brin Is Back in the Trenches at Google]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>联合创始人正在与科技巨头总部的人工智能研究人员一起工作，协助建立强大的 Gemini 系统<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001071343"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="577" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-821144?width=860&amp;height=577" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">谷歌联合创始人谢尔盖·布林长期以来对人工智能技术很感兴趣，他定期与参与人工智能研究的谷歌员工会面。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：JUNG YEON-JE/​​法新社/Getty Images </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001071343"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/miles-kruppa" itemprop="url" rel="author">迈尔斯·克鲁帕</a></span>和<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/deepa-seetharaman" itemprop="url" rel="author">迪帕·西塔拉曼</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 7 月 21 日上午 10:10（东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/sergey-brin-google-ai-gemini-1b5aa41e"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>谷歌联合创始人谢尔盖·布林重返工作岗位。</p><p>近几个月来，这位亿万富翁每周都会访问这家科技巨头位于加州山景城的办公室，通常每周三到四天，与研究人员一起努力开发该公司的下一个大型人工智能系统。</p><p>知情人士称，布林去年年底参加了谷歌办公室有关人工智能的会议，但他参与的频率和强度有所增加。他的新立场与他在 2019 年<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/sundar-pichai-to-replace-larry-page-as-ceo-of-alphabet-11575409229?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">辞去</a>母公司<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/GOOG" class="company-name">Alphabet</a>高管职务后采取的相对不干涉的态度发生了显着变化。</p><p>他与一组研究人员密切合作，构建了谷歌期待已久的人工智能模型 Gemini。他们讨论了诸如“损失曲线”之类的技术问题，这是一种衡量人工智能程序随时间推移表现的方法，布林还每周与谷歌员工就新的人工智能研究进行讨论。知情人士称，他还干预人事事务，例如聘用受欢迎的研究人员。</p><p>现任和前任员工表示，布林在谷歌的影响力增加反映了人工智能的关键时刻以及他对这项技术的长期兴趣。谷歌是该技术的先驱，但在将其转化为新产品方面比竞争对手慢。</p><p>随着 Meta Platforms 等公司<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/meta-and-microsoft-team-up-to-distribute-new-ai-software-for-commercial-use-c4f7b634?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">最近推出的新产品</a>，人工智能研究领域的竞争正在加剧。谷歌<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/google-tries-to-catch-up-to-rivals-like-openai-as-they-release-viral-apps-11674828418?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">加快了产品开发速度，</a>以应对去年发布的 ChatGPT，这是一款由<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/MSFT" class="company-name">微软</a>支持的研究公司 OpenAI 开发的人工智能聊天机器人，可以流畅地响应一系列书面查询。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-820793?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">谷歌创始人谢尔盖·布林和拉里·佩奇从斯坦福大学博士生起就一直在一起工作。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：迈克尔·内格尔/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>Gemini 是 Google 尝试构建的<a href="https://blog.google/technology/ai/google-palm-2-ai-large-language-model/" target="_blank" class="icon none">通用人工智能</a>程序，可以与<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/openai-rolls-out-updated-version-of-viral-chatbot-chatgpt-f03fea27?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">OpenAI 的 GPT-4 模型</a>相媲美，该模型为 ChatGPT 的付费版本提供支持。据知情人士透露，负责该项目的谷歌高管德米斯·哈萨比斯 (Demis Hassabis) 在最近的一次全公司会议上告诉员工，该项目将于今年晚些时候推出。</p><p> 49 岁的布林于 1998 年与拉里·佩奇 (Larry Page) 一起创立了谷歌，他们在斯坦福大学攻读博士时共同进行了网络搜索研究。</p><p>虽然布林近年来偶尔出现在谷歌总部，但他的注意力主要集中在飞艇和新形式的灾难援助等外部利益上，以及捐赠部分巨额财富的努力。根据 S&amp;P Capital IQ 的数据，他是 Alphabet 的第二大个人股东，仅次于 Page，所持股份价值接近 900 亿美元。</p><p>自从谷歌在 5 月份的年度开发者大会上宣布一系列人工智能产品以来，Alphabet 的股价已经上涨了 10% 以上，其中包括新版本的核心搜索引擎，该引擎提供了冗长的摘要并邀请后续问题。这一涨幅与竞争对手微软的股价和更广泛的纳斯达克综合指数大致一致。</p><p>知情人士称，布林大部分时间都在新建的查尔斯顿东大楼里与山景城的人工智能研究人员坐在一起，该大楼距离谷歌公司园区原来的中心仅几步之遥。谷歌和 Alphabet 的首席执行官桑达尔·皮查伊 (Sundar Pichai) 也在大楼内设有办公室。</p><p>四年前，当创始人辞去日常职务并将皮查伊提拔为 Alphabet 首席执行官时，他们表示将定期与他交谈并提供“建议和关爱，但不会每天唠叨”。他们仍然控制着 Alphabet 的多数投票权，并与皮查伊一起担任执行董事会委员会成员。</p><p>据一位了解皮查伊想法的人士透露，皮查伊对布林的参与感到兴奋，并鼓励他做出贡献。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="475" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-820792?width=700&amp;height=475" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> 2012 年，谢尔盖·布林 (Sergey Brin) 与一辆自动驾驶汽车在谷歌山景城总部。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：贾斯汀·沙利文/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>谷歌在人工智能领域处于领先地位，于 2011 年成立了一个名为 Brain 的研究部门，研究如何使用称为深度学习的计算技术来构建广泛有用的人工智能程序。</p><p> Pichai 今年<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/alphabets-google-combines-ai-research-units-brain-and-deepmind-620f4f7d?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">将 Brain 团队与 DeepMind 合并</a>，DeepMind 是一家人工智能研究公司，此前在 Alphabet 旗下独立运营。这次改组将 DeepMind 联合创始人哈萨比斯提升为合并后的 Google DeepMind 集团的首席执行官。</p><p>现任和前任员工表示，一些研究人员接受了布林的参与，认为这是对他们工作的认可，也是人工智能团队在过渡时期的有益干预。哈萨比斯和许多 Google DeepMind 高管在伦敦工作，使该办公室成为新设置中事实上的权力中心。</p><p>自 11 月份 ChatGPT 发布以来，布林的参与度不断增加。据《纽约时报》早些时候报道的知情人士透露，谷歌的联合创始人参加了会议，审查谷歌正在为 5 月份的开发者大会准备的人工智能产品。</p><p>此后，布林一直在谷歌总部保持着强大的影响力，经常出席研究聚会和公司庆祝活动。谷歌表示，除了联合创始人和董事会成员之外，布林在公司没有正式的新角色。布林的发言人没有回应置评请求。</p><p>佩奇在管理谷歌期间有时是一个隐居的人物，而布林却培养了一个更平易近人的形象，穿着溜冰鞋穿越总部，在公司的各个项目之间穿梭。</p><p>据与布林有过互动的人士透露，自从去年<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/google-in-talks-to-invest-200-million-into-ai-startup-11666381180?&amp;mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">人工智能热潮</a>以来，布林就参加了该公司的发布会，该公司推广了图像生成程序 Stable Diffusion，并且偶尔也会参加在加利福尼亚州希尔斯伯勒一座价值 6800 万美元的豪宅（即 AGI House）举行的活动。 AGI 代表通用人工智能，即计算机程序有一天可以与人类推理相匹配。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="507" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-820384?width=700&amp;height=507" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">今年早些时候，谷歌首席执行官桑达尔·皮查伊、谢尔盖·布林、卢森堡首相泽维尔·贝特尔和谷歌全球事务总裁肯特·沃克。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：卢森堡国务部</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>今年3月，在<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/posts/xavier-bettel_thanks-to-sundar-pichai-and-kent-walker-activity-7041634974231351296-hDnQ/" target="_blank" class="icon none">卢森堡首相访问期间，布林被拍到与皮查伊和谷歌全球事务总裁肯特·沃克在谷歌总部合影</a>，布林身着灰色运动裤和黑色长袖衬衫。其他与会者都穿着西装。</p><p>布林与 Gemini 的合作是谷歌长期努力构建人工智能系统的又一成果，这些系统可以展现出类人的能力，并更无缝地满足该公司数十亿用户的需求。</p><p>布林在 2017 年 <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ffvu6Mr1SVc&amp;t=92s" target="_blank" class="icon none">世界经济论坛上接受采访</a>时表示，起初，布林忽视了 Brain 团队的工作，并对他们能否破解人工智能表示怀疑，尽管该团队始于他领导的 Google X 部门。</p><p> “说实话，我根本没有注意它，”布林说。他说，几年后，Brain 的研究被用于谷歌许多最大的产品，颠覆了他之前的假设。</p><p>布林在一定程度上关注了人事问题，随着人工智能研究人员的人才争夺战加剧，这对谷歌和其他大型科技公司来说是一个困难的领域。 2017 年，谷歌发表了一篇具有里程碑意义的论文，该论文被誉为引发了最新一波人工智能发展浪潮，该论文的多位作者已离开该公司，为竞争对手的初创公司筹集数亿美元资金。</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>谢尔盖·布林会让谷歌在人工智能领域更具竞争力吗？加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p>现任和前任员工表示，尽管布林是世界上最受尊敬的计算机科学家之一，但他需要赶上人工智能的最新发展，并且没有为编码项目做出重大贡献。</p><p>布林在 2018 年发布的上一封股东信中宣传了人工智能的可能性，他写道，“计算解决重要问题的力量和潜力从未如此强大。”</p><p> “人工智能的新春天是我一生中计算领域最重大的发展，”他写道。</p><p>写信给 Miles Kruppa ( <a href="mailto:miles.kruppa@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">miles.kruppa@wsj.com)</a>和 Deepa Seetharaman ( <a href="mailto:deepa.seetharaman@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">deepa.seetharaman@wsj.com</a> )</p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 21 Jul 2023 14:10:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/sergey-brin-google-ai-gemini-1b5aa41e</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/sergey-brin-google-ai-gemini-1b5aa41e<author><![CDATA[Miles KruppaDeepa Seetharaman]]></author><category> WSJ公司</category><category>专有的</category><category>人工智能技术</category><category>市场研究/公共关系</category><category>公共关系</category><category>互联网搜索引擎</category><category>广告/营销/公共关系</category><category>商业/消费者服务</category><category>在线服务提供商</category><category>技术</category><category>新产品/服务</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>产品与服务</category><category>人工智能/机器学习</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>计算机科学</category><category>高净值个人</category><category>科学/人文</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>字母</category><category>谷歌</category><category>元平台</category><category>梅塔</category><category>谢尔盖·布林</category><category>新产品</category><category>服务</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>产品</category><category>人工智能</category><category>机器学习</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>计算机科学</category><category>高净值个人</category><category>科学</category><category>人文学科</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>人工智能技术</category><category>市场调查</category><category>公共关系</category><category>互联网搜索引擎</category><category>广告</category><category>营销</category><category>商业</category><category>消费服务</category><category>在线服务提供商</category><category>技术</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[U.S. Soldier’s Crossing Into North Korea Points to Security Gaps]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>特拉维斯·金本应登上飞往德克萨斯州的航班，然后才出现在非军事区的一个旅游景点<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001073010"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-821490?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">美国士兵特拉维斯·金在韩国面临袭击指控。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：社交媒体/VIA REUTERS </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001073010"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/dasl-yoon" itemprop="url" rel="author">达斯尔·尹</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 21 日上午 9:21 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-soldiers-crossing-into-north-korea-points-to-security-gaps-576b7733"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>首尔——特拉维斯·金原定于周一乘坐美国航空的航班从韩国起飞。他从来没有成功过。</p><p>相反，在德克萨斯州面临潜在军事纪律处分的美国士兵一天后最终<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/north-korea-us-national-custody-b53b4449?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">越境进入朝鲜</a>，一系列事件引发了人们对非军事区旅游景点的安全措施以及美军对金计划离开的处理的质疑。</p><p>朝鲜尚未回应美国就金的地位与该政权接触的努力。金是一名 23 岁的陆军二等兵。 “坦率地说，我担心他，”陆军部长克里斯汀·沃穆斯周四在阿斯彭举行的一次会议上表示。</p><p>据美国和机场官员称，金在韩国<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/travis-king-u-s-soldier-held-in-north-korea-had-been-detained-in-south-korea-4cded529?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">面临袭击指控</a>，周一由美国军人护送到仁川机场，登上美国航空飞往德克萨斯州的航班。他将在德克萨斯州受到军官的会面，并面临纪律处分和可能的开除。</p><p>据机场官员称，在通过机场的安全检查站后，金告诉航空公司工作人员他找不到自己的护照。随后他被护送至出发侧。从那里，他似乎趁机溜出了机场。</p><p>第二天，他出现在联合安全区的参观中，该区域位于<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-officer-on-a-pink-phone-dials-down-north-korea-tensions-11558287392?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">非军事区内</a>，是游客可以到达的距离朝鲜最近的区域。</p><p>韩国国家安全委员会前官员千成勋 (Cheon Seong-whun) 表示：“美国军方将不得不重新评估安全措施，特别是在管理在海外面临指控的士兵方面。” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=D69C17D9-A239-4491-A945-60AAB8A04205&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fu-s-soldiers-crossing-into-north-korea-points-to-security-gaps-576b7733&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">白宫新闻秘书表示，周二，一名美国陆军一等兵特拉维斯·金 (Travis King) 士兵在参观联合安全区时越过军事分界线，随后美国正在​​与朝鲜当局合作。照片：安东尼·华莱士/法新社/盖蒂图片社<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>据一位知情人士透露，金被护送至海关，但飞机上没有美国军人陪同，因为他在韩国拘留所服刑后不再​​被视为罪犯。驻韩美军发言人没有立即回应置评请求。</p><p>去年，金在韩国的两起不同事件中面临袭击指控，之后被拘留了近 50 天。在十月的第二起事件中，据称他踢坏了一辆警车。 2月份，他因该事件被罚款4,000美元。</p><p>沃穆斯说：“他在韩国袭击了一个人，并被韩国政府拘留，他将返回美国并在军队中承担后果。” “我确信他正在努力解决这个问题。”</p><p>金是在参观联合安全区（也称为板门店）时穿越的，该地区一直是军事谈判、和平谈判和囚犯交换的场所。联合安全区位于非军事区内，沿线 150 英里由铁丝网和地雷把守。</p><p>在联合安全区，分隔朝鲜两国的唯一障碍是一条很容易被踩过去的短砖线。前总统<a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/donald-trump">唐纳德·特朗普</a>于 2019 年这样做，成为<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/trump-says-north-koreas-kim-wants-to-meet-11561862697?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">第一位进入朝鲜的在任总统</a>，当时他在那里会见了朝鲜领导人<a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/kim-jong-un">金正恩</a>。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="525" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-820431?width=700&amp;height=525" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">据路透社报道，身穿黑色衬衫、头戴帽子的特拉维斯·金 (Travis King) 是周二访问韩国非军事区的游客之一，随后他穿越了边境。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：莎拉·莱斯利/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>尽管保安人员驻扎在联合安全区的韩国一侧，但他们被禁止越过界限进入朝鲜追捕某人。 2017年，一名朝鲜士兵冲过边境，其他朝鲜士兵向他开枪。但根据朝韩军事协议，自 2018 年以来，共同安全区的所有警卫都没有携带武器。</p><p>首尔官员表示，金可能不得不提前计划对联合安全区的访问。 7月10日，他被从拘留所释放。一周后，他被护送至仁川机场。旅游机构通常在旅行前一周接受参观联合安全区的申请，以获得负责监督联合安全区的美国领导的联合国司令部的许可。</p><p> King 参加了由韩国 HanaTour ITC 公司运营的非军事区全日游。该旅游团专门为美国军人提供联合安全区旅游，但金为普通游客单独预订了旅游。 HanaTour ITC 拒绝就所涉及的安全程序或金如何逃往朝鲜发表评论。</p><p>要进入非军事区，韩国或美国士兵通常会根据导游提交的名单上的姓名验证身份。一名韩国官员表示，尽管美军在联合安全区巡视，但仍不知道他的行踪，这对军方来说是“巨大的尴尬”。</p><p>在平壤和华盛顿之间紧张局势加剧之际，金现在掌握在朝鲜手中。朝鲜拒绝与美国进行正式会谈，并就其与首尔的军事演习以及部署韩国核资产对华盛顿进行了猛烈抨击。本周，一艘能够发射核弹头的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-nuclear-capable-boomer-sub-visits-south-korea-for-first-time-in-decades-dc4a8187?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">美国潜艇</a>四十年来首次抵达韩国港口。</p><p>前韩国国家安全委员会官员千说，朝鲜可能需要一些时间来调查金越境的动机以及他是否可以成为该政权有用的宣传资产。</p><p>美国官员表示，他们正试图通过多种渠道与朝鲜建立联系，其中包括设有与朝鲜相连的热线的联合国司令部，以及为在朝鲜的美国公民提供领事服务的瑞典。</p><p> “我们尚未成功与朝鲜取得联系，”沃穆斯说。 “我们想让他回到美国。我担心他们会如何对待他。”</p><p> —<em>道格·卡梅伦对本文做出了贡献。</em></p><p>写信给 Dasl Yoon，邮箱为<a href="mailto:dasl.yoon@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">dasl.yoon@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 21 Jul 2023 13:21:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/us-soldiers-crossing-into-north-korea-points-to-security-gaps-576b7733</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/us-soldiers-crossing-into-north-korea-points-to-security-gaps-576b7733<author><![CDATA[Dasl Yoon]]></author><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[How a Tiny Archipelago Gave Russia a Foothold in the Atlantic]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>长期捕鱼协议对法罗群岛的经济至关重要，但它也让俄罗斯船只能够进入北大西洋<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001072705"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="572" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-821413?width=860&amp;height=572" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">法罗群岛的克里斯蒂安港。渔业是其支柱产业之一。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：法新社，盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001072705"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/sune-engel-rasmussen" itemprop="url" rel="author">苏尼·恩格尔·拉斯穆森</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 21 日上午 8:46 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/how-a-tiny-archipelago-gave-russian-ships-a-foothold-in-the-atlantic-83e9c31d"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>尽管自俄罗斯入侵乌克兰以来，欧洲一直在努力缩小安全漏洞，但北大西洋的一个小岛群为俄罗斯船只在其水域和港口捕鱼和停靠提供了漏洞，其中包括被指控从事间谍活动和破坏活动的船只。</p><p>西方国家对法罗群岛及其周边地区发生的事情越来越警惕，法罗群岛是丹麦王国的一个自治领土，与莫斯科签订了长期渔业协议。该协议允许俄罗斯船只停靠法罗群岛港口，绕过欧盟港口的禁令。</p><p>它还赋予俄罗斯船只在法罗群岛和英国共享水域的捕鱼权，促使英国政府敦促法罗群岛暂停捕鱼权——而法罗群岛领导人尚未同意这样做。</p><p>这场争端表明，欧洲在入侵乌克兰后进入了与俄罗斯发生大国冲突的新时代，因此加强了对<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/russian-submarines-test-nato-in-icy-north-atlantic-11593682201?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">北海和北大西洋航道</a>的关注。</p><p>法罗群岛-英国特区位于格陵兰岛、冰岛和英国之间的战略过境路线“GIUK 缺口”内，自冷战以来一直是北大西洋军事行动的关键入口。随着各国越来越依赖海上能源设施和<a href="https://www.wsj.com/podcasts/wsj-the-future-of-everything/melting-ice-undersea-cables-how-the-arctic-is-getting-fast-internet/2a204ef7-e522-45cb-946c-44fc1e4600d7?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">海底光缆</a>来实现互联网接入和金融交易，这一差距的重要性也随之增加。</p><p> “海底关键基础设施和能源基础设施已经成为目标，未来也将成为目标。华盛顿特区威尔逊中心极地研究所所长丽贝卡·平卡斯 (Rebecca Pincus) 表示，美国和欧洲去年已经意识到了这一点。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-821416?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">英国格里姆斯比码头上的一艘渔船。英国和法罗群岛共享一些捕鱼水域。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：奥利·斯卡夫/法新社/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>在受到英国的批评后，法罗群岛上周实施了新的限制，这意味着只有双边协议中指定的 31 艘俄罗斯船只可以进入其港口。此前，协议中未提及的其他俄罗斯渔船可以在法罗群岛港口合法转运货物或接受维修。法罗外交部长Høgni Hoydal在接受采访时表示，新举措将使俄罗斯船只数量减少约60%。</p><p>然而，根据1999年与丹麦达成的协议，俄罗斯船只仍将能够在法罗群岛与英国共享的所谓特区内捕鱼，英国当局不得在那里检查它们。</p><p>根据《华尔街日报》通过信息自由请求获得的一封信，英国食品、农业和渔业大臣马克·斯宾塞 (Mark Spencer) 一月份告诉法罗群岛同行丹尼斯·霍尔姆 (Dennis Holm)，“与俄罗斯续签协议的决定影响了我们的双边关系”，并表示“严重关切这种情况可能在 2023 年再次出现”。</p><p>英国政府发言人表示，伦敦将继续寻求禁止俄罗斯船只在英国-法罗群岛特别海域捕鱼。</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/whos-killing-off-residents-of-this-island-nation-crime-writers-1524243819?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">饱经风霜的法罗群岛</a>拥有 54,000 人口、70,000 只羊和大约 50 万对海雀，拥有自己的贸易政策管辖权，并且不是欧盟成员国，但其外交和安全政策由丹麦决定。法罗群岛与俄罗斯的渔业协议可追溯到 1977 年，该协议允许法罗群岛人主要在巴伦支海捕捞鳕鱼，俄罗斯人则可以在法罗群岛水域捕捞鲱鱼和鲭鱼。鱼品约占<a href="http://www.wsj.com/articles/faeroe-islands-boom-by-selling-salmon-to-russia-1424483776" target="_blank" class="icon none">法罗群岛出口额的 90%</a> 。丹麦政界人士表示，该协议使法罗群岛乃至丹麦容易受到俄罗斯间谍活动的影响，并与欧盟产生裂痕。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-821415?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">马克·斯宾塞表示，英国政府对法罗群岛与俄罗斯的协议感到担忧。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Justin Ng/Zuma Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-warned-ukraine-not-to-attack-nord-stream-7777939b?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">去年波罗的海北溪管道遭到的破坏</a>表明了水下基础设施的脆弱性以及识别肇事者的难度。例如，英国77%的天然气是通过北海海底管道从挪威进口的。</p><p>伦敦国际战略研究所海军和海上安全高级研究员尼克·柴尔兹表示：“俄罗斯投入了大量资金，能够威胁这些地区并开展秘密海底活动。” “它又重新流行起来了。”</p><p>最近发生的事件引发了欧洲各国首都对俄罗斯在法罗群岛的存在的焦虑。</p><p>去年，一条连接挪威卫星站与大陆的2.6英里长的海底光缆被切断并消失得无影无踪，海洋跟踪数据显示，一艘俄罗斯拖网渔船在光缆被切断前的几天里在该光缆上来回穿梭了140多次，引发了破坏活动的怀疑。挪威媒体首先报道了这艘拖网渔船的动向。</p><p>事件发生后，拖网渔船 Melkart-5 一直停靠在法罗群岛，直到今年 5 月。 Melkart-5 号所有者 Murman SeaFood 副总监安德烈·罗曼 (Andrey Roman) 否认该船参与破坏活动的指控。</p><p> “我们公司是一家完全商业化的公司，”罗曼说。 “我们的船只在挪威港口和公海上受到挪威当局的控制。”</p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p>去年11月，挪威警方在希尔科内斯北部港口搜查了从法罗群岛直接抵达那里的两艘俄罗斯拖网渔船Lira和Ester，并在锁着的门后发现了苏联时代的军用无线电设备。挪威该地区情报负责人当时告诉国家媒体，他怀疑这些船只可能参与间谍活动。</p><p>根据海上贩运数据，这两艘船目前的应答器已关闭，但自 2015 年以来已在法罗群岛停靠了 200 多次。根据法罗群岛渔业检查提供的名单，它们都是获准停靠法罗群岛港口的 31 艘船只之一。</p><p>挪威警察安全局发言人拒绝就针对三艘俄罗斯船只的指控发表评论，但表示挪威是俄罗斯情报部门的目标，“显然，包括民用船只在内的船只可能被俄罗斯当局用作收集信息的平台，作为其活动的一部分。”</p><p>法罗群岛外交部长霍伊达尔表示，法罗群岛当局没有发现俄罗斯船只在其水域进行任何恶意活动。他还指出，这些岛屿与俄罗斯的贸易并不违反欧盟<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/in-shadow-of-sanctions-russia-courts-friends-boasts-resilience-at-flagship-economic-forum-d299b6bc?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">对莫斯科的制裁</a>，其中不包括食品——尽管目前没有欧盟国家与俄罗斯进行鱼类贸易。</p><p> “自从俄罗斯在乌克兰发动战争以来，我们实施了与欧盟相同的制裁，”霍伊达尔说。 “但我们遵守我们的协议。”</p><p>哥本哈根的法罗群岛议员 Sjurdur Skaale 表示，欧盟应取消对法罗群岛加工海鲜产品出口的关税，以帮助法罗群岛减少与俄罗斯的贸易，并暂停该协议。</p><p> 2014 年，法罗群岛在入侵克里米亚后选择不遵守欧盟对俄罗斯的制裁，从而获得了进入俄罗斯市场的特权。然而，冰岛——另一个依赖海鲜业务的小领土——效仿欧盟，成为俄罗斯反制裁的目标。次年，冰岛经济萎缩约1%。</p><p> “对于较小的国家和地区来说，风险很高，”平卡斯说。</p><p>写信给 Sune Engel Rasmussen： <a href="mailto:sune.rasmussen@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">sune.rasmussen@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 21 Jul 2023 12:46:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/how-a-tiny-archipelago-gave- Russian-ships-a-foothold-in-the-atlantic-83e9c31d</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/how-a-tiny-archipelago-gave- Russian-ships-a-foothold-in-the-atlantic-83e9c31d<author><![CDATA[Sune Engel Rasmussen]]></author><category>乌克兰</category><category>农业</category><category>钓鱼</category><category>港口/港口运营</category><category>水路运输/航运</category><category>运输/物流</category><category>法规/政府政策</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>贸易/外部支付</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国际制裁</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>间谍</category><category>贸易壁垒/限制</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>乌克兰</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>规定</category><category>政府政策</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>贸易</category><category>外部支付</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国际制裁</category><category>政治</category><category>间谍</category><category>贸易壁垒</category><category>限制</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>农业</category><category>钓鱼</category><category>港口</category><category>港口作业</category><category>水运</category><category>船运</category><category>运输</category><category>后勤</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Russia Boosts Rates as Ukraine War Costs Mount]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>经济正处于拐点。卢布贬值、工资飙升以及债务推动的国家支出激增，重新引发了通胀压力。 <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001072660"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="460" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-821289?width=700&amp;height=460" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">俄罗斯中央银行总部。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：尤里·科切特科夫/Shutterstock </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001072660"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/paul-hannon" itemprop="url" rel="author">保罗·汉农</a></span>和<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/georgi-kantchev" itemprop="url" rel="author">格奥尔基·坎切夫</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 7 月 21 日上午 8:32（东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/russia-raises-rates-as-ukraine-war-costs-mount-a41bfa23"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>俄罗斯央行周五上调了关键利率，这是自入侵乌克兰后不久以来的首次，以应对<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/russias-big-economic-problem-not-enough-workers-d5164d47?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">劳动力短缺</a>、 <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/russias-ruble-slides-on-capital-flight-fears-9d86273e?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">卢布贬值</a>和通胀复苏等经济<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/russia-races-to-plug-budget-gap-as-oil-revenues-fall-and-war-costs-rise-6f3c8c5?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">困难的新时期</a>。</p><p>俄罗斯经济去年陷入衰退，但由于石油和天然气收入的暴利、国家救济以及迅速<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/russia-set-to-overtake-saudi-arabia-in-battle-for-chinas-oil-market-6435742e?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">将贸易从欧洲转向亚洲的</a>能力，在西方制裁的冲击下幸存下来。经济学家预计俄罗斯今年将实现正增长。</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>您认为俄罗斯经济前景如何？加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p>但利率的新一轮上涨——幅度超出预期——表明<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/russias-economy-is-starting-to-come-undone-431a2878" target="_blank" class="icon none">经济目前正处于拐点</a>。去年支撑它的因素已经减少，新的压力又出现了。</p><p>凯投宏观(Capital Economics)高级新兴市场经济学家利亚姆·皮奇(Liam Peach)表示：“俄罗斯的宏观经济稳定性现在比战争爆发以来的任何时候都更加脆弱。”</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/wagner-prigozhin-putin-mutiny-moscow-march-7072d6ea?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">瓦格纳雇佣军集团上个月叛变流产</a>导致货币贬值，工资飙升以及债务推动的国家支出激增，重新引发了通胀压力，导致加息成为必要。</p><p>虽然俄罗斯的总体通胀率看似较低，6 月份同比仅为 3.25%，但较 5 月份的 2.5% 大幅上升。去年入侵后冲击造成的高比较基数掩盖了价格上涨的大部分内容。最近的每周数据超出预期，经济学家预测未来几个月消费者价格将大幅上涨。</p><p>周五，为了阻止通胀上升，央行将利率从 7.5% 提高了整整一个百分点至 8.5%。经济学家此前预计利率将上涨0.5个百分点。</p><p> “近几个月来，经济形势发生了巨大变化，”俄罗斯央行行长埃尔维拉·纳比乌林娜 (Elvira Nabiullina) 告诉记者。 “人员短缺问题变得更加严重。卢布已经走弱。价格压力一直在加剧。”</p><p>纳比乌利纳表示，可能会进一步加息，幅度取决于未来的经济发展。</p><p>俄罗斯央行表示，今年经济可能增长 1.5% 至 2.5%，高于 4 月份预测的 0.5% 至 2%。</p><p>然而，增长的上升显示了俄罗斯的局限性，特别是当它争先恐后地为乌克兰战争提供资源和人力时，乌克兰战争现已进入第二年。</p><p>国际货币基金组织估计，俄罗斯的潜在增长率（即在通胀不上升的情况下经济增长的速度限制）在 2014 年（即俄罗斯从乌克兰手中夺取克里米亚）之前约为 3.5%。一些经济学家表示，限速现已降至 1% 以下。 </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><img width="600" height="800" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-821438?width=600" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p>与战争相关的支出给国库带来了压力，今年上半年国家预算严重亏损。为了应对不断膨胀的赤字，政府表示将实施开支削减。</p><p>芬兰银行新兴经济研究所所长伊卡·科霍宁表示：“战争迫使政府放弃之前的财政保守政策，增加支出，这支撑了经济增长。”</p><p>俄罗斯财政部副部长周二表示，战争成本导致俄罗斯债务负担增加。</p><p>据官方通讯社塔斯社报道，伊琳娜·奥克拉德尼科娃在俄罗斯议会上院的一次会议上表示：“我们将增加债务，这是一个无望的局面。” “我们必须这样做，因为我们的支出正在增长，我们必须支持经济……我们必须支持军事集团。” </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"><img width="600" height="800" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-821421?width=600" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p>由于西方制裁导致原油价格下跌和俄罗斯石油价格大幅折扣，今年上半年的能源预算收入与去年相比几乎减少了一半。俄罗斯的经常账户盈余（衡量流入经济的资金的广义指标）已从去年同期的 767 亿美元缩减至今年第二季度的 54 亿美元。</p><p>贸易恶化以及六月兵变后的不确定性使卢布成为今年全球表现最差的货币之一，兑美元汇率下跌约 18%。据央行称，俄罗斯人在叛乱期间撤回了 1000 亿卢布（约合 11 亿美元）。货币贬值会增加进口成本，引发通货膨胀。</p><p>劳动力市场是另一个压力点：俄罗斯企业已经受到严峻的人口前景的压力，现在正经历 90 年代以来最严重的工人短缺，数百万人逃离该国或被动员参加战争。</p><p><a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/MCO" class="company-name">穆迪</a>分析公司经济学家奥尔加·比奇科娃表示：“劳动力、生产和金融资源的竞争正在加剧。” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="449" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-821291?width=700&amp;height=449" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">人们在莫斯科一家大卖场购物。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：Maxim Shipenkov/ZUMA Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>货币疲软、贸易平衡恶化和劳动力紧缩的结合反过来又推高了通货膨胀。</p><p> “加上卢布贬值的延迟影响，这将在未来几个月推高价格，”她说。</p><p>经济学家表示，经济生产能力向军事的转变是俄罗斯今年能够避免更严重的衰退并实现增长的一个重要因素。</p><p>第一季度政府支出占GDP的比重比去年同期增长13.5%，这是自1996年以来的最高增幅。</p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p>虽然官方统计数据没有公布军工产量，但今年前五个月“金属成品”（分析师称该产品包括武器和弹药）的产量比去年增长了 26%。据说包括军事产量在内的其他行业也蓬勃发展：计算机、电子和光学产品的产量增长了 22%，而特种服装的产量则增长了 84%。相比之下，汽车产量同比下降 18.5%。</p><p>分析人士表示，从长远来看，制裁影响的不断加大、俄罗斯的国际孤立和劳动力紧缩严重削弱了增长前景。</p><p>科尔霍宁表示：“尽管俄罗斯到目前为止比预期更好地经受住了制裁，但从整体情况来看，我们不能乐观。”</p><p>写信给 Paul Hannon <a href="mailto:paul.hannon@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">（paul.hannon@wsj.com）</a>和 Georgi Kantchev（ <a href="mailto:georgi.kantchev@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">georgi.kantchev@wsj.com）</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 21 Jul 2023 12:32:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/ Russia-raises-rates-as-ukraine-war-costs-mount-a41bfa23</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/ Russia-raises-rates-as-ukraine-war-costs-mount-a41bfa23<author><![CDATA[Paul HannonGeorgi Kantchev]]></author><category> gfx-contrib</category><category>欧洲华尔街日报</category><category>乌克兰</category><category>法规/政府政策</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>经济表现/指标</category><category>经济增长/衰退</category><category>通货膨胀数字/价格指数</category><category>货币政策</category><category>利率</category><category>贸易/外部支付</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国际制裁</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>贸易壁垒/限制</category><category>军事行动</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>规定</category><category>政府政策</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>经济表现</category><category>指标</category><category>经济增长</category><category>经济衰退</category><category>通货膨胀数字</category><category>价格指数</category><category>货币政策</category><category>利率</category><category>贸易</category><category>外部支付</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>国际关系</category><category>国际制裁</category><category>政治</category><category>风险新闻</category><category>贸易壁垒</category><category>限制</category><category>军事行动</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Beijing Rushes to Shore Up Battered Private Economy. Skepticism Abounds.]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>中国誓言要促进因多年监管打压和流行病控制而摇摇欲坠的私营部门，但投资者并不相信<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001072909"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-821472?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">重庆的招聘会。中国重振私营部门的努力可能会加剧青年失业</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：法新社/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001072909"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/stella-yifan-xie" itemprop="url" rel="author">Stella Yifan Xie</a></span> （香港）和<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/raffaele-huang" itemprop="url" rel="author">Raffaele Huang</a></span> （新加坡）</div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 21 日上午 8:32 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/beijing-rushes-to-shore-up-battered-private-economy-skepticism-abounds-80c1a23c"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>随着<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinas-economy-barely-grows-as-recovery-fades-5652a92a?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">刚刚起步的经济复苏步履蹒跚</a>，中国领导层向陷入困境的私营部门提供了广泛的支持。</p><p>但经济学家和投资者表示，仅靠宏大的宣言和言辞是不够的。国内需求疲软，加上人们普遍认为北京仍然偏爱国有企业，这意味着私营企业主（这个群体<a href="https://www.wsj.com/livecoverage/china-xi-jinping-communist-party-congress/card/in-china-the-state-sector-is-in-private-sector-stutters-jyOYiDqUFiSBISBHVyyS?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">对经济活力和招聘发挥了大部分作用</a>）的情绪不太可能扭转，至少在短期内不会。</p><p>在本周的一份高调声明中，中国共产党和国家内阁联合公布了一份包含 30 多项指导方针的清单，誓言要让私营部门“做大、做优、做强”。有关部门表示，这些措施将在私营企业和国有企业之间提供公平的竞争环境，承诺打破市场壁垒，扩大对私营企业的融资，并让它们参与未来的政策咨询。</p><p>北京向私营部门——这个部门贡献了中国总产出的约60%和城市就业的80%——之际，正值世界第二大经济体的增长在多个方面放缓之际。这也标志着前三年的缓和，在这三年中，中国官员通过一系列监管打压和严格限制，重创了课外教育和房地产等行业。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-821477?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">西安的一条卡车生产线。中国领导层推出了刺激汽车销售的激励措施。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：FLORENCE LO/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>周三公布的这些措施得到了<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/TCEHY" class="company-name">腾讯控股</a>低调联合创始人马化腾等几位知名企业家的公开赞扬。这家视频游戏和社交媒体巨头以及其他主要互联网公司的业务和利润都因过去两年北京突然的监管变化而受到重创。</p><p>过去几周，中国官员对投资者和商界给予了大量关注，并公开承诺支持该行业。中国总理李强会见了<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/BABA" class="company-name">阿里巴巴集团和 TikTok 母公司字节跳动</a>等中国最大科技公司的高管，鼓励他们通过创新支持经济。</p><p>官员们还会见了当地制造业和消费领域的商界领袖，调查他们面临的困难，并举行会议，向美国、欧洲和日本的商协会保证，该国仍然对外国投资开放。他们还推出了促进汽车销售的激励措施。</p><p>此类支持是在中国互联网公司自 2020 年底以来市值损失超过 1 万亿美元之后出台的，当时当局取消了金融科技巨头蚂蚁集团的大规模首次公开募股，启动了一系列监管打压行动。今年政府对贝恩公司等全球咨询公司的突击搜查以及反间谍法的扩大版本也挫伤了商界的动物精神。</p><p>尽管如此，接受《华尔街日报》采访的经济学家和私营企业家表示，三年来<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-covid-dropped-restrictions-reopen-xi-11673534796?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">对 Covid-19 的严格控制</a>以及同时进行的监管活动已经造成了损失。<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/UBS" class="">牛津</a>大学助理研究员、瑞银集团前首席经济学家乔治·马格努斯表示，最近中国互联网和私人补习行业的清洗让企业家们担心会意外地与共产党的社会目标发生冲突<span class="company-name-type">。</span></p><p></p><p> “对私营部门的总体态度仍然是服从国家利益，”他说。</p><p>私营企业和投资者的谨慎态度在很大程度上也反映出长期经济阻力，例如该国人口减少以及地方政府和家庭债务上升。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-821478?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">浙江省的一处建筑工地。中国房地产市场持续的痛苦可能会恶化投资者的情绪。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：hector retamal/法新社/盖蒂图片社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>总部位于华盛顿特区的智库彼得森国际经济研究所（PIIE）即将发布的一份研究报告显示，按市值计算，中国100家最大上市公司中私营企业的份额从2021年中期55%的峰值下降至今年6月的39%，接近三年多来的最低水平。</p><p> 2023 年上半年，私营部门投资同比下降 0.2%，这是自 2005 年开始收集官方数据以来首次出现收缩，但 2020 年除外，当时经济受到疫情的严重打击。相比之下，同期国有控股企业投资增长8.1%。</p><p>私营部门企业的利润更容易受到出口下降和消费者支出疲软的影响，今年前五个月的利润下降了 21%。国有企业利润下降17.7%。</p><p>中国房地产市场持续的痛苦可能会恶化投资者的情绪。 PIIE 研究员黄天雷表示，房地产开发商的投资可能约占私人投资的三分之一。</p><p>北京方面重燃商业信心的风险很大。如果未能重振境况不佳的私营部门，北京可能进一步无法实现 5% 左右的全年增长目标。它还可能加剧本已很高的青年失业率。</p><p>多年来，私营企业，特别是科技、教育和房地产行业的私营企业吸纳了中国很大一部分大学毕业生。</p><p>分析人士表示，多年来这些行业的监管收紧以及房地产市场的持续低迷已经导致年轻专业人士的职业机会枯竭，导致中国6月份的青年失业率达到创纪录的21.3%。</p><p>经济学家表示，从长远来看，私营部门的退出将降低整体效率并导致生产率增长放缓，其后果可能最终抑制中国的增长潜力。</p><p>一家专注于技术投资的私募股权公司驻北京合伙人张旋表示，北京最近承诺支持私营部门向投资者发出了积极的信息，但并没有让他放心遏制更广泛的经济衰退。</p><p> “The long-term performance of the market can&#39;t simply be governed by a couple policy documents,” he said.</p><p class="articleTagLine"> —Xiao Xiao in Beijing contributed to this article.</p><p> Write to Stella Yifan Xie at <a href="mailto:stella.xie@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">stella.xie@wsj.com</a> and Raffaele Huang at <a href="mailto:raffaele.huang@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">raffaele.huang@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 21 Jul 2023 12:32:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/beijing-rushes-to-shore-up-battered-private-economy-skepticism-abounds-80c1a23c</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/beijing-rushes-to-shore-up-battered-private-economy-skepticism-abounds-80c1a23c<author><![CDATA[Stella Yifan XieRaffaele Huang]]></author><category>法规/政府政策</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>经济表现/指标</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category> ByteDance</category><category>规定</category><category>政府政策</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>经济表现</category><category>指标</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[The Rise and Fall of the Chief Diversity Officer]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> Diversity executives hit the exits as company priorities shift; &#39;everything is a battle&#39; <!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001071159"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-820139?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> From left: Melinda Starbird, a human resources and diversity executive; Dani Monroe, former CDO for Mass General Brigham; and Miriam Warren, CDO for Yelp.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo Illustration: Melinda Starbird, Cheryl Richard, Yelp </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001071159"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/te-ping-chen" itemprop="url" rel="author">Te-Ping Chen</a></span> and <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/lauren-weber" itemprop="url" rel="author">Lauren Weber</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> July 21, 2023 7:00 am ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chief-diversity-officer-cdo-business-corporations-e110a82f"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p> Two years ago chief diversity officers were some of the hottest hires into executive ranks. Now, they increasingly feel left out in the cold.</p><p> Companies including <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/NFLX" class="">Netflix</a> <span class="company-name-type">,</span> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/DIS" class="company-name">Disney</a> and <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/WBD" class="company-name">Warner Bros. Discovery</a> have recently said that high-profile diversity, equity and inclusion executives will be leaving their jobs. Thousands of diversity-focused workers have been laid off since last year, and some companies are <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/diversity-workplace-affirmative-action-dei-3646683b?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">scaling back</a> racial justice commitments.</p><p> Diversity, equity and inclusion—or DEI—jobs were put in the crosshairs after many companies started re-examining their executive ranks during the tech sector&#39;s shake out last fall. Some chief diversity officers say their work is facing additional scrutiny since the Supreme Court <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/supreme-court-rules-against-affirmative-action-c94b5a9c?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">struck down affirmative action</a> in college admissions and companies brace for <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/republican-attorneys-general-warn-top-u-s-businesses-over-discrimination-1eb78d29?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">potential legal challenges</a> . DEI work has also become a <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ron-desantiss-education-policies-leave-florida-teachers-feeling-unsure-3a81a236?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">political target</a> .</p><p> “There&#39;s a combination of grief, being very tired, and being, in some cases, overwhelmed,” says Miriam Warren, chief diversity officer for <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/YELP" class="">Yelp</a> <span class="company-name-type">,</span> of the challenges facing executives in the field.</p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p> In interviews, current and former chief diversity officers said company executives at times didn&#39;t want to change hiring or promotion processes, despite initially telling CDOs they were hired to improve the talent pipeline. The quick about-face shows company enthusiasm for diversity initiatives hasn&#39;t always proved durable, leaving some diversity officers now questioning their career path.</p><p> In the wake of George Floyd&#39;s murder in police custody in May 2020, companies scrambled to hire chief diversity officers, changing the face of the C-suite. In 2018, less than half the companies in the S&amp;P 500 employed someone in the role, and by 2022 three out four companies had created a position, according to a study from Russell Reynolds, an executive search firm.</p><p> Once mostly tasked with HR matters, today&#39;s diversity leaders are expected to weigh in on new product development, marketing efforts and current events that have an impact on how workers and consumers are feeling. Warren and other CDOs said the expanded remit is playing out in a politically divided environment where corporate diversity efforts are the subject of frequent <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/companies-new-cause-dodging-the-culture-wars-73e52cf3?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">social-media firestorms</a> .</p><h3> Falling demand</h3><p> New analysis from employment data provider Live Data Technologies shows that chief diversity officers have been more vulnerable to layoffs than their human resources counterparts, experiencing 40% higher turnover. Their job searches are also taking longer.</p><p> “I got to 300 applications and then I stopped tracking,” says Stephanie Lubin, who was laid off from her role as diversity head at Drizly, an online alcohol marketplace, in May following the company&#39;s acquisition by <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/UBER" class="">Uber</a> <span class="company-name-type">.</span></p> In one case, Lubin says she went through 16 rounds of interviews for a role she didn&#39;t get, and says she is now planning to pivot out of DEI work.<p></p><p> The number of CDO searches is down 75% in the past year, says Jason Hanold, chief executive of Hanold Associates Executive Search, which works with Fortune 100 companies to recruit HR and DEI executives, among other roles. Demand is the lowest he has seen in his 30 years of recruiting.</p><p> At the same time, he says, more executives are feeling skittish about taking on diversity roles.</p><p> “They&#39;re telling us, the only way I want to go into another role with DEI is if it includes something else,” he says of the requests for broader titles that offer more responsibilities and resources. He estimates that 60% of diversity roles he is currently filling combine the title with another position, such as chief human resources officer, up from about 10% five years ago.</p><p> During the pandemic, some companies moved people into diversity leadership if they were an ethnic minority, says</p> Dani Monroe, even when they weren&#39;t qualified. Monroe served as CDO for Mass General Brigham, a Boston-based hospital system and one of the largest employers in the state, until 2021 and convenes a yearly gathering of more than 100 CDOs.<p></p><p> “These were knee-jerk reactions,” she says of the hurried CDO hires, adding that some of those elevations didn&#39;t create much impact, leaving both sides feeling disillusioned.</p><h3> On-the-job obstruction</h3><p> American workers are split on the importance of a diverse workforce, <a href="https://www.pewresearch.org/social-trends/2023/05/17/diversity-equity-and-inclusion-in-the-workplace/" target="_blank" class="icon none">surveys find</a> .</p><p> Diversity chiefs also encounter obstruction from top executives, says Melinda Starbird, a human resources and diversity executive who has worked at <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/T" class="">AT&amp;T</a> <span class="company-name-type">,</span></p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/SBUX" class="company-name">Starbucks</a> and OfferUp, an online marketplace. Leaders sometimes associate diversity efforts with mandates, such as the equal-employment rules that apply to federal contractors. Those requirements for compliance can create executive resistance that bleeds over into other cultural or policy shifts, such as <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/biden-to-sign-bill-making-juneteenth-a-federal-holiday-11623944038?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">adding Juneteenth</a> as a company holiday, she says.<p></p><p> “Even if you report to the CEO, it&#39;s still a battle and it&#39;s a smaller budget,” says Starbird, who was laid off from OfferUp in November during a broader restructuring.</p><p> Many diversity executives feel a lack of buy-in from their colleagues. In <a href="https://urldefense.com/v3/__https://world50.com/impact?utm_source=wsj&amp;utm_medium=pr&amp;utm_campaign=2023idreport__;!!F0Stn7g!EGLdSj-lMiFGnMwE-GKlWcgVj1tXMu0_-ZbTIyBUUYuQV0JylSZhtrfPiJ-A4c5JWSBx3Po2kxjQHsQPCw$" target="_blank" class="icon none">a survey</a> of 138 diversity executives conducted this spring by World 50 Group, a networking organization for corporate leaders, 82% said they had sufficient influence to do their job, down 6 percentage points from 2022. Asked if they felt supported by middle managers, 41% said yes, an 8-percentage-point drop.</p><p> Since the Supreme Court overturned affirmative action in June, companies are anticipating spillover legal action could have an impact on them. Those that are still hiring CDOs want people who can help the board navigate the political and legal landscape of diversity work and figure out how to take defensive moves to shield them from litigation, says Tina Shah Paikeday, global leader of Russell Reynolds&#39;s diversity, equity and inclusion practice.</p><p> “They recognize it would be smart to get ahead of that.” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="467" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-820155?width=700&amp;height=467" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> David Kenny, chief executive of Nielsen, says efforts to restructure compensation to make it more equitable created a backlash.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Nielsen</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> People are more resistant to company-backed efforts to advance diversity when they are worried about their own jobs, whether because of impending layoffs or disruptions from AI, says David Kenny, chief executive of Nielsen, the media-ratings company.</p><p> Kenny was both CEO and CDO for a time, <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chief-executive-or-diversity-chief-nielsens-ceo-is-both-11608908446?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">taking on</a> the diversity role to emphasize how important it was to the future of the business. Even as CEO, it could be a tough sell. Efforts to restructure compensation to make it more equitable created a backlash.</p><p> “A lot of it is, &#39;I&#39;m losing my slice of the pie,&#39; ” he says. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/newsroom-feedback/9d40dc7b-c819-4785-ab9c-4c1e1272d3a7.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p> Write to Te-Ping Chen at <a href="mailto:Te-ping.Chen@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">Te-ping.Chen@wsj.com</a> and Lauren Weber at <a href="mailto:Lauren.Weber@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">Lauren.Weber@wsj.com</a> </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/bef2e1de-18c2-41e5-86fb-8b21bfe3c1c7.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 21 Jul 2023 11:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/chief-diversity-officer-cdo-business-corporations-e110a82f</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/chief-diversity-officer-cdo-business-corporations-e110a82f<author><![CDATA[Te-Ping ChenLauren Weber]]></author><category> WSJ生活工作</category><category>WSJ公司</category><category>Human Resources Consulting</category><category> Broadcasting</category><category> Cable Broadcasting</category><category> Accounting/Consulting</category><category>商业/消费者服务</category><category>商业咨询</category><category>媒体/娱乐</category><category>劳工/人事</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>Workplace Diversity</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category> Netflix</category><category> NFLX</category><category>华特迪士尼</category><category>DIS</category><category>美国电话电报公司</category><category>时间</category><category>华纳兄弟探索公司 A 系列</category><category>世界BD</category><category>华纳兄弟探索公司</category><category>劳动</category><category>人员</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>workplace diversity</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>human resources consulting</category><category> broadcasting</category><category> cable broadcasting</category><category>会计</category><category>咨询</category><category>商业</category><category>消费服务</category><category>business consultancy</category><category>媒体</category><category>娱乐</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[U.K. Prime Minister Sunak Suffers Election Setback]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>选民在两次特别选举中拒绝保守党，反映出对通货膨胀、高税收和糟糕的公共服务的愤怒<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001072718"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="589" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-821436?width=860&amp;height=589" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">英国反对党工党的基尔·马瑟在周四塞尔比和安斯蒂地区的特别选举中获胜。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：丹尼·劳森/祖玛出版社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001072718"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/humza-jilani" itemprop="url" rel="author">Humza Jilani</a></span>和<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/max-colchester" itemprop="url" rel="author">Max Colchester</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 21 日上午 6:37 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-k-prime-minister-sunak-suffers-election-setback-e4438ee1"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>伦敦——英国执政的保守党在两个据点的特别选举中失利，选民对<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-k-s-stubborn-inflation-means-more-pain-for-homeowners-renters-94f44e96?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">英国经济停滞</a>和高通胀表示愤怒，并指出首相里希·苏纳克在明年的大选中可能面临的挑战。</p><p>塞尔比和安斯蒂——保守党根基深厚的地区——的失利反映了这个国家的不满情绪，这个国家的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/nhs-uk-national-health-service-strike-costs-11675693883?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">公共服务摇摇欲坠</a>，税收达到70年来的最高水平， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/bank-of-england-interest-rates-fb6332a6?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">抵押贷款成本</a>急剧上升。在西南选区萨默顿和弗罗姆，中间派自由民主党以 29 个百分点的优势夺得了保守党上次赢得的席位。</p><p> Ipsos 的数据显示，全国民意调查显示反对党工党领先保守党 22 个百分点。</p><p>周四举行的特别选举也暴露了英国脱欧后保守党选举联盟中的分歧。 2019年，保守党通过将英格兰北部的蓝领、脱欧友好和对移民持怀疑态度的前工党选民与南部更传统、富裕的保守党联合起来<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/britain-votes-in-an-election-that-will-set-the-course-of-brexit-11576156488?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">，赢得了绝大多数席位</a>。最新结果显示，这个选民基础正在分裂。</p><p>这三场特别选举是为了取代三名退出议会的保守党议员，其中包括前首相<a href="https://www.wsj.com/topics/person/boris-johnson">鲍里斯·约翰逊</a>，后者<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ex-british-leader-boris-johnson-quits-as-lawmaker-ahead-of-partygate-report-767a4baa?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">辞职是</a>为了抗议议会的一份报告，该报告发现他在 Covid-19 期间故意向议员撒谎。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819965?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">英国首相里希·苏纳克表示，本周的结果显示下届大选尚未“板上钉钉”。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：英国议会/JESSICA TAYLOR/via REUTERS</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>最大的挫折发生在英格兰北部的塞尔比，工党推翻了自二战以来一直投票给保守党的一个席位。 2019 年，保守党以 35 个百分点的优势获胜。</p><p> “很明显，变革的需求有多么强烈，”工党领袖凯尔·斯塔默(Keir Starmer)在选举结果公布后表示。苏纳克警告说，结果表明，可能于明年秋季举行的大选尚未“板上钉钉”。</p><p>苏纳克在乌克斯布里奇获得了缓刑，乌克斯布里奇是伦敦西部的一个地区，以前由约翰逊控制。保守党仅以 495 票之差保住了该席位，超出了他们将输掉选票的预期。当地人对计划扩大对进入该地区的旧车辆征收污染税的愤怒提供了足够的反弹，使保守党能够继续掌权。</p><p>周四的损失凸显了苏纳克在兑现他的承诺方面的努力，这些承诺包括修复英国饱受罢工困扰的国有化医疗服务、遏制非法移民以及控制七国集团中最高的通货膨胀率。</p><p>前高盛银行家苏纳克将自己标榜为一名技术官僚，他可以解决这些弊病，并带领他的政党在必须于 2025 年初举行的大选中实现创纪录的连续第五个任期。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=8721652E-C4D0-4BCA-A94F-5BE086258F7E&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Fu-k-prime-minister-sunak-suffers-election-setback-e4438ee1&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption"> Core inflation is rising in the UK while falling in other big economies like the US WSJ&#39;s Anna Hirtenstein explains why, and how it affects Prime Minister Rishi Sunak&#39;s goal of halving inflation by the end of 2023. Illustration: Daniel Orton/WSJ<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>但时间已经不多了。民意调查专家、上议院保守党议员罗伯特·海沃德表示，“如今，保守党在经济问题上没有可信度，里希在明年大选之前很快就能解决这个问题”。</p><p>英国的高通胀是由于就业市场紧张给工资带来上行压力，以及俄罗斯 2022 年初入侵乌克兰造成的食品和能源价格持续飙升。</p><p>然而，周三公布的数据显示，6月份通胀率跌至15个月低点7.9%，降幅超出预期，这对政府承诺在年底前将通胀率降至5%的承诺来说是一个令人鼓舞的迹象。与苏纳克关系密切的官员表示，数据表明，到举行选举时，实际工资可能会上涨。这可能使保守党能够在选举前实施减税，以推动英国摆脱停滞的增长率。</p><p>但通货膨胀并不是政府唯一的政治难题。公共服务多年来一直遭受资金不足、过度拥挤和近年来工人罢工浪潮的困扰。等待国家医疗服务体系治疗的人数已激增至超过 700 万人。罢工工人迫使学校关闭和公共交通取消。</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>总理里希·苏纳克（Rishi Sunak）能否在下次大选前扭转他的政党局面？加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p>与此同时，苏纳克承诺停止移民船只穿越英吉利海峡。今年到目前为止，已有近 14,000 名移民乘坐小艇从法国航行到英国海岸，略少于去年同期的 15,280 人。</p><p>周四的所有三场选举均在大多数选民投票支持 2016 年脱离欧盟的选区进行——这是保守党主张的立场。但大批选民仍然坚决反对该党，因为该党将其政治身份押注于实现英国脱欧所承诺的成果。</p><p> 2016年至2017年担任阿克斯布里奇选区当地市长的约翰·亨斯利(John Hensley)生平第一次投票反对保守党。</p><p>与大多数阿克斯布里奇选民一样，他也于 2016 年投票决定离开欧盟，因为英国脱欧将腾出数亿英镑用于国民医疗服务体系 (NHS) 和其他基本服务。</p><p>但他长达数月的等待看医生的时间、不断增加的食品杂货账单以及对政府丑闻的沮丧，让他对自己一生的政党和英国脱欧感到不满。</p><p> “我的投票向政府发出了一个信号，表明我们不能继续这样下去，”他说。</p><p>写信给 Humza Jilani <a href="mailto:humza.jilani@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">(humza.jilani@wsj.com)</a>和 Max Colchester ( <a href="mailto:Max.Colchester@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">Max.Colchester@wsj.com)</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 21 Jul 2023 10:37:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/uk-prime-minister-sunak-suffers-election-setback-e4438ee1</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/uk-prime-minister-sunak-suffers-election-setback-e4438ee1<author><![CDATA[Humza JilaniMax Colchester]]></author><category>经济表现/指标</category><category>政府财政</category><category>政府预算/税收</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国际关系</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>选举</category><category>国家/总统选举</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>里希·苏纳克</category><category>经济表现</category><category>指标</category><category>政府财政</category><category>政府预算</category><category>税收</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国际关系</category><category>政治</category><category>国内政治</category><category>选举</category><category>国家的</category><category>总统选举</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Untangling the U.S. From China’s Economy Is Messy]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>珍妮特·耶伦的“朋友外包”推动因供应链纵横交错而变得复杂<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001071011"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="574" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-819897?width=860&amp;height=574" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">作为美国稳定关系努力的一部分，财政部长珍妮特·耶伦本月访问了北京。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：托马斯·彼得/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001071011"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/andrew-duehren" itemprop="url" rel="author">安德鲁·杜伦</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">美国东部时间 2023 年 7 月 21 日上午 5:30 </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/untangling-the-u-s-from-chinas-economy-is-messy-8a658f2e"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>越南河内——事实证明，拜登政府通过外科手术式切断与中国经济关系的尝试很难执行。</p><p>美国财政部长珍妮特·耶伦本周访问了越南，讨论她推动的“ <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/yellen-calls-for-friend-shoring-trade-to-diversify-from-china-11658200959?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">友岸外包</a>”，她用这个术语呼吁企业将供应链从中国转移到更友好的国家。过去五年，美国和越南之间的贸易额呈爆炸式增长，从 2018 年的 600 亿美元增至 2022 年的约 1400 亿美元。</p><p> “我们看到了深化这些关系的巨大潜力，”耶伦在参观河内一家依赖中国零部件的工厂时表示。她在访问期间与越南总理范明正和其他共产党官员的会面中多次赞扬了两国不断发展的关系。</p><p>厘清中国在全球供应链中的角色，即使是在有限的领域，也绝非易事。近年来，美国从<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-imported-more-cars-phones-supplies-from-abroad-9157aca6?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">中国进口的商品份额有所下降</a>，而从其他亚洲国家进口的份额则有所扩大。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><div class="media-object-video"><div class="wsj-media-summary clearfix"><div class="strap-container"><h4 class="strap" itemprop="description"></h4></div></div><iframe width="400" height="225" src="https://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/v3/iframe.html?guid=EA224A41-9ED5-4FFE-94DD-F6BDB9AE59AB&amp;height=225&amp;width=400&amp;plid=video_amp&amp;chainVideos=true&amp;parentUrl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Famp%2Farticles%2Funtangling-the-u-s-from-chinas-economy-is-messy-8a658f2e&amp;a=a" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe><p class="imageCaption">美国财政部长珍妮特·耶伦周日结束对中国的访问时表示，双方在应对经济和国家安全紧张局势方面正在取得进展。她补充说，世界上最大的两个经济体脱钩是“不可能的”。照片：Mark R. Crisino/Zuma Press<span class="imageCredit">
        
        
        </span></p></div></div><p>越南或韩国等许多替代贸易伙伴本身就与中国有着紧密的联系。中国在清洁能源技术方面的主导地位使得拜登政府对于推动企业完全避开中国产品犹豫不决。准确识别美国及其盟国认为中国构成威胁的行业具有挑战性。</p><p>本月早些时候，耶伦在北京<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/yellen-says-u-s-doesnt-seek-winner-take-all-fight-with-china-72ab3c95?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noreferrer noopener">告诉中国同行</a>，美国的目标是减少关键领域对中国的敞口，同时不损害对两国有利的贸易和投资流动。</p><h3>友好伙伴与中国保持密切联系</h3><p>越南的生产在很多情况下仍然涉及中国公司。</p><p>在河内，耶伦参观了生产电动摩托车的 Selex Motors 工厂。该公司首席执行官表示，该公司使用中国供应商生产电动机以及一些电子连接器、开关和减震器。他说，公司80%的供应来自当地。</p><div class="media-object scope-web
          wrap
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>美国是否应该继续寻求与中国经济脱钩？为什么或者为什么不？加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div><p>越南已成为美国太阳能电池板的重要供应国</p><p>不过，商务部的一项调查发现， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinese-solar-manufacturers-dodged-u-s-tariffs-probe-finds-11669952820?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">中国公司通过将产品改道越南和其他三个东南亚国家来规避关税</a>。</p><p>这一发现将使来自越南和其他国家的太阳能电池板征收大幅更高的关税，但拜登政府因担心美国太阳能电池板成本上涨<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/biden-administration-to-waive-solar-import-tariffs-for-two-years-11654525408?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">而推迟了征税</a></p><p>一位财政部高级官员表示，中国企业并未参与美国和越南之间贸易增长的大部分，并指出越南有利的经济条件推动了经济增长。</p><p>美国<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/new-ev-rules-mean-fewer-models-eligible-for-tax-credit-98b6b63c?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">为帮助消费者购买电动汽车提供</a>新补贴，旨在减少对中国的依赖，同时减少碳排放，但也面临着类似的挑战。为了获得补贴资格，汽车的电池必须主要由来自美国或其自由贸易伙伴之一的零部件和矿物制成。中国不是这样的合作伙伴。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="468" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-820752?width=700&amp;height=468" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">拜登总统去年参观了韩国三星半导体工厂。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：乔纳森·恩斯特/路透社</p></figcaption></figure></div><h3>美国尚未确定哪些公司值得关注</h3><p>即将出台的规则将进一步完善这些要求，禁止使用包含来自“相关外国实体”的任何材料的电池。</p><p>无论拜登政府广泛定义“受关注外国实体”以包括许多中国供应商，还是更狭隘地将其仅针对某些公司，都将对信贷的可用性产生巨大影响。 <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/china-controls-minerals-that-run-the-worldand-just-fired-a-warning-shot-at-u-s-5961d77b?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">中国公司在电池组件的制造和其中的矿物供应方面占据主导地位</a>。在不久的将来，将中国产品完全从供应链中剔除对于汽车制造商来说可能是不可能的。一些美国公司甚至<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ford-invests-3-5-billion-in-michigan-battery-plant-with-chinese-partners-technology-1aed174c?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">计划与中国公司合作</a>生产电池。</p><p>耶伦在接受采访时表示，定义“受关注的外国实体”“相当复杂”，并补充说，财政部的规则将保持在《通胀削减法案》的范围内。</p><p> “但在有一定范围的地方，我们当然要记住，我们不想让它变得不可能——过于关注供应链的弹性，以至于我们无法实现让汽车上路的任何目标，”耶伦说。</p><p>在其他清洁能源补贴方面，拜登政府制定的规则对采购要求的规定比一些美国制造商所希望的更为宽松，为在补贴清洁能源建设中使用中国供应扫清了道路。尽管美国实施出口管制，拜登政府还<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-to-allow-south-korean-taiwan-chip-makers-to-keep-operations-in-china-5d7d72cc?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">允许韩国和台湾的顶级半导体制造商</a>继续向中国销售产品。</p><p>拜登政府还在制定<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-grapples-with-potential-threats-from-chinese-ai-7d1f2e70?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">限制美国对华部分投资</a>的新规则，但仍在整理这些规则如何适用于美国公司的外国子公司等细节。这些限制将适用于美国在半导体、量子计算和人工智能领域的私募股权和风险投资，禁止对这些领域的某些投资，同时要求披露其他领域的投资。</p><p>该命令的目的是<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-prepares-new-rules-on-investment-in-technology-abroad-a451e035?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">阻止美国投资者</a>帮助中国公司开发可用于在军事对抗中对抗美国或其盟友的技术。</p><p> “这还没有最终决定，所以我不想说它会发生，但我相信它会发生，而且我认为今年夏天最有可能发生，”耶伦在接受采访时谈到新的投资规则时表示。</p><p>美国正在鼓励其欧洲盟友采取类似措施来保护供应链并限制北京获得西方专业知识。事实证明，找到正确的平衡点对他们来说也很困难。</p><p> “我们需要与中国进行贸易，同时我们需要让关键的战略供应链更加安全，”欧盟经济委员保罗·真蒂洛尼(Paolo Gentiloni)在接受采访时表示。 “说起来简单，但实际操作起来并不明显。”</p><p>写信给安德鲁·杜伦 (Andrew Duehren)，邮箱为<a href="mailto:andrew.duehren@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">andrew.duehren@wsj.com</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 21 Jul 2023 09:30:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/untangling-the-us-from-chinas-economy-is-messy-8a658f2e</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/untangling-the-us-from-chinas-economy-is-messy-8a658f2e<author><![CDATA[Andrew Duehren]]></author><category>电气元件/设备</category><category>Industrial Electronics</category><category>工业品</category><category>技术</category><category>法规/政府政策</category><category>企业/行业新闻</category><category>供应链</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>珍妮特·耶伦</category><category>规定</category><category>政府政策</category><category>公司的</category><category>行业新闻</category><category>供应链</category><category>经济新闻</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>会展行业新闻过滤器</category><category>电气元件</category><category>设备</category><category>工业电子</category><category>工业品</category><category>技术</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Jackie O.’s Collection of Homes Was as Iconic as It Gets]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div> A massive East Hampton estate. A sprawling New York City apartment. The properties where she lived before and after becoming first lady are some of the most coveted real estate in America <figure><img src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818403/?width=1278&amp;size=1" alt="Jacqueline Kennedy Onassis, pictured in 1960, lived in an iconic collection of luxury homes." referrerpolicy="no-referrer"><figcaption> Jacqueline Kennedy Onassis, pictured in 1960, lived in an iconic collection of luxury homes. The Estate of Jacques Lowe/Getty Images <span>The Estate of Jacques Lowe/Getty Images</span> </figcaption></figure><!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001055379"></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001055379"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline"> By <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/eb-solomont" itemprop="url" rel="author">EB Solomont</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1"> Updated July 21, 2023 12:00 am ET </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/jackie-o-s-collection-of-homes-was-as-iconic-as-it-gets-2500daf4"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bigtophero
"></div><p> When Eaddo and Peter D. Kiernan III first laid eyes on Hammersmith Farm in Newport, RI, in the 1990s, they loved it immediately.</p><p> Immortalized as the site of the 1953 wedding reception of Jacqueline Bouvier Kennedy and John F. Kennedy, and later dubbed President Kennedy&#39;s summer White House, the circa-1880s estate overlooking Narragansett Bay hadn&#39;t been lived in for decades. But Kiernan, a self-described patriot who said he knew the late John F. Kennedy Jr. , realized instantly it would be the perfect summer home for his own sprawling Irish Catholic family.</p><p> The Kiernans purchased Hammersmith Farm for just over $8 million in 1999, and then spent more than 10 years restoring it, drawing on old sketches, photographs and stories shared by Jackie&#39;s stepbrother, Hugh D. “Yusha” Auchincloss III, whose family built the estate about a century before. “We would literally say, &#39;Tell us everything you can remember,&#39; ” said Kiernan, a former Goldman Sachs banker. When Auchincloss saw the finished renovation, Kiernan said, he wept. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="534" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-820716?width=700&amp;height=534" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Hammersmith Farm, in Newport, RI</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Carol M. Highsmith/Buyenlarge/Getty Images</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> “There are pretty houses in the Hamptons and in Nantucket, but we wanted to do something that was authentically connected to what had gone on here for a very long time,” Kiernan said.</p><p> Born into wealth, Jacqueline Bouvier Kennedy Onassis lived in homes ranging from apartments in New York City to houses in Georgetown and estates in Newport, Virginia and Martha&#39;s Vineyard. Many were legacy properties that, nearly 30 years after Jackie&#39;s death, still command top-dollar among luxury buyers drawn to their classical style, history and aesthetic.</p><p> In Washington, DC, real-estate agent Jamie Peva of Washington Fine Properties said homes tied to Jackie and John Kennedy can command a roughly 10% premium even in Georgetown, a historic neighborhood full of notable residents. “It might be a conversation starter that [former Secretary of State Henry] Kissinger lived there, but it doesn&#39;t translate into money unless it&#39;s the Kennedys,” he said.<br><br> Peva said it helps that the couple—along with their families and later, Jackie herself—owned exceptional homes in prime locations. “The house they went to the White House from was one of the most important houses in Georgetown,” Peva said. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="722" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818423?width=700&amp;height=722" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> The Kennedys, pictured in 1961, lived in Georgetown before moving to the White House.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Bettmann Archive/Getty Images</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Jackie&#39;s name is an instant draw and marketing boon, said Eileen O&#39;Neill of the Corcoran Group, who is marketing Lasata, one of her childhood homes in the Hamptons, for $55 million. But provenance only goes so far, O&#39;Neill said, and Lasata&#39;s classic elegance and exacting renovations by the recent owners have drawn interest from potential buyers. “Comparable sales and the climate of the market is really what dictates price,” she said.</p><p> That was the case when Jackie&#39;s childhood apartment at 740 Park Avenue in Manhattan sold for $25.25 million in 2017, said Jeremy Stein of Sotheby&#39;s International Realty, who was involved in the deal. The buyer was banking heir Jacob M. Safra, records show. “The building speaks for itself,” said Stein, citing location, architecture and a long history of prominent residents, including Jackie. “It remains this iconic, great building that has a cachet, but it lives up to the cachet,” he said.</p><p> Read on for a closer look at notable properties tied to Jackie over the years, based on property records, multiple biographies and the accounts of real-estate agents. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          smallrule
"><div class="wsj-article-page-rule"></div></div><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bleed
"><img width="600" height="1184" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/0c296686-a760-4b9d-a314-09cc321612ca-fallback_app.jpg" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p> As a young child, Jackie spent summers at a lavish East Hampton estate owned by her paternal grandfather, John Vernou Bouvier Jr. Known as Lasata, meaning “place of peace” in the Algonquin language of the native Montaukett people, the estate sat on roughly 14 acres. It was set back from Further Lane and had a long, curving drive and 15-room manor built in the 1910s, according to the book “Jacqueline Bouvier Kennedy Onassis: A Life” by Donald Spoto. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          wrap
"><figure class="media-object-image img-wrap"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="639" height="511" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818420?width=639&amp;height=511" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Jackie, left, spent summers in East Hampton in homes owned by her grandparents.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Bettmann Archive/Getty Images</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> When designer Reed Krakoff and his wife, interior designer Delphine Krakoff, bought the property in 2007, the manor hadn&#39;t been renovated in years, Reed Krakoff said. The Krakoffs paid $25 million for two parcels totaling about 11 acres, records show. The couple spent nearly two years restoring the house, using building techniques and materials original to the home, he said. They restored single-pane glass windows and instead of sheetrock walls they used three-coat plaster on metal lathe. They also refurbished and restored all of the existing hardware and fixtures, he said. (For example, the bathtubs are porcelain over iron.)</p><p> Krakoff said there is a “mystique” to owning a famous property, but the real draw was the house itself. “It&#39;s a really rare thing to find a beautiful, historic house that hasn&#39;t been altered in a way that takes away from the authenticity,” he said. The couple, who have restored around 15 homes, uncovered and restored original oak-paneled walls from the Bouviers&#39; time under Louis XV-style paneling added later. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          edgetoedge
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/019dae13-6292-447b-ba02-4bbb620702e5.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p> Around 2017, the Krakoffs subdivided the property and sold it in two parts. A neighbor purchased a nearly 4-acre parcel with a sunken tennis court for $11.25 million. David Zander, a television, commercial and film producer based in Los Angeles, paid $24 million in 2018 for a roughly 7.2-acre parcel comprising the main house, a swimming pool, pool house, guesthouse, caretaker&#39;s cottage and a garage with a workshop.</p><p> Zander said the scale, proportion and aesthetics of the home drew him in—not the Jackie connection. “If Jackie lived in a hovel would I be interested in buying it? No,” he said. But he admitted that over time, the connection became interesting. “Through a house, you become a small part of American history,” he said. Zander said he has repaired structural issues and made other improvements to the home, including adding a glass front door so that visitors can see through the house to the garden.</p><p> <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/jackie-os-childhood-hamptons-home-lists-for-55-million-8187989c?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none" rel="noopener">The property</a> also has a visual easement in front to maintain a view of the house from the street. “It&#39;s a significant historical structure for all to enjoy,” Zander said. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          smallrule
"><div class="wsj-article-page-rule"></div></div><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bleed
"><img width="600" height="1184" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/da99f27d-8cc1-479d-a3b0-40bff490d707-fallback_app.jpg" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p> When she wasn&#39;t at Lasata, Jackie and her parents summered at Wildmoor, a circa-1800s house in East Hampton owned by her paternal grandfather, who let his son and daughter-in-law stay there rent-free, according to multiple accounts. The house, located a few houses down from Grey Gardens, the famed estate once owned by Jackie&#39;s cousins, was a “charming old wooden-frame structure, clapboarded and shingled, with a widow&#39;s walk overlooking acres of potato fields, a cattail swamp, and the distant, roaring Atlantic,” according to John H. Davis&#39; 1993 book “The Kennedys: Dynasty and Disaster.” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="909" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818419?width=700&amp;height=909" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Jackie and her parents lived rent-free at Wildmoor, which was owned by her grandfather.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Bettmann Archive/Getty Images</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Later, the abstract expressionist Adolph Gottlieb and his wife, Esther Gottlieb, purchased Wildmoor and turned a free-standing carriage house into an art studio. Around 1990, the attorney Richard D. Spizzirri purchased the property; his estate sold it for $6.8 million in 2021, records show. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          edgetoedge
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/ac9e37b1-b5b9-4344-9f66-72586e6c854d.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p> David Tosher, a residential design consultant who advised the buyer, said the roughly 5,700-square-foot house with six bedrooms hadn&#39;t been renovated in decades. The wood on the bottom of the house was rotten from sitting in mud for decades and “the house was held there by the grace of God,” he said. The kitchen was “uneatable,” a glass atrium was leaking and at some point, portions of the elevator shaft were blocked off and removed, rendering it useless, he said. Tosher said workers took apart the house and rebuilt it entirely in a slightly different location farther from the road. They kept the original framing but added a full basement. They also used old photographs to restore original features including the main staircase, some doors and a gooseneck-curved railing. “We rebuilt everything but left the history,” Tosher said. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          smallrule
"><div class="wsj-article-page-rule"></div></div><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bleed
"><img width="600" height="1184" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/30ae4b25-5ebc-42d2-9413-17f5d1421fa2-fallback_app.jpg" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p> As a child in the 1930s, Jackie lived with her parents at 740 Park Avenue, an elegant, limestone-clad building designed by Rosario Candela. The building was developed by Jackie&#39;s maternal grandfather, James T. Lee, who let his daughter, Janet Lee Bouvier, and son-in-law, John Vernou “Black Jack” Bouvier III, live there rent-free, according to multiple accounts.</p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          wrap
"></div><p> Flamboyant but cash-strapped, Jackie&#39;s father gutted the kitchen and added gold-plated fixtures to the bathroom, according to Michael Gross&#39; “740 Park: The Story of the World&#39;s Richest Apartment Building.” But his finances were such that he couldn&#39;t afford to furnish it when he was done, leaving open space for Jackie and her sister to roller-skate through what became one of New York City&#39;s most iconic buildings, according to the book.</p><p> Today the apartment is owned by Jacob M. Safra, an heir to a banking fortune, who purchased it for $25.25 million in 2017, records show. The sellers, hedge funder David Ganek and his wife, Danielle Ganek, renovated the duplex and had it on the market for several years, asking as much as $44 million in 2014.</p><p> Stein of Sotheby&#39;s, who represented the seller, said the Kennedy and Bouvier cachet is real although the building itself is the main draw for most buyers. “The building speaks for itself,” he said. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          smallrule
"><div class="wsj-article-page-rule"></div></div><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bleed
"><img width="600" height="1184" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/f82f3f77-7910-4471-a9fa-c600419fd530-fallback_app.jpg" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p> Jackie moved to Merrywood in the 1940s after her mother married Standard Oil heir Hugh D. Auchincloss Jr., according to Spoto&#39;s “A Life.” Located on the banks of the Potomac River, the estate is about 8 miles from downtown Washington with a Georgian-style house spanning more than 16,000 square feet.</p><p> By the 1960s, Auchincloss, facing financial constraints, agreed to sell Merrywood, then spanning about 46 acres, for $650,000 to real-estate developers and brothers Sheldon and Ira Magazine, according to Jan Pottker&#39;s 2002 book “Janet and Jackie: The Story of a Mother and Her Daughter, Jacqueline Kennedy Onassis.” The Magazine brothers&#39; plans to build 1,030 high-rise apartments on the site sparked “an enormous cry” among neighbors, the book said. After the deal went through in 1963, the Kennedy White House took steps to block the high-rise development. “Jackie sparked it,” said the book, citing her commitment to preservation and environmental causes. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="553" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818405?width=700&amp;height=553" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Jackie lived at Merrywood, pictured in 1962, following her mother&#39;s marriage to owner Hugh D. Auchincloss Jr.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: ASSOCIATED PRESS</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> In 1965, the Magazine brothers sold the entire property for $650,000 to real-estate developer C. Wyatt Dickerson and his then-wife, Nancy Dickerson, who retained the main residence and more than 7 acres and built about 46 smaller homes on the remaining land, according to “Janet and Jackie.” In 2005, AOL co-founder Steve Case bought the 7-acre original manor residence for a then-record sum of $24.5 million, records show. Thirteen years later, he sold it for $43 million to the Kingdom Saudi Arabia, the government of which expressed “tremendous respect” for the home&#39;s place in American history in a statement at the time.</p><p> Marc C. Lowham of TTR Sotheby&#39;s International Realty, who was involved in the 2018 deal, said the property&#39;s location and provenance made it one of the most timeless and valuable estates in the area. Many original details remain, including the basic floor plan and elaborate plaster moldings. The gated estate also has formal gardens, a swimming pool and tennis court. “The Jackie Kennedy legacy there still feels very much alive,” he said. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          smallrule
"><div class="wsj-article-page-rule"></div></div><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bleed
"><img width="600" height="1184" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/5880d3e8-cd01-470a-a46e-56bfd86537af-fallback_app.jpg" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p> In 1953, Jackie and John Kennedy&#39;s 1,200-person wedding reception took place at Hammersmith Farm, an estate overlooking Narragansett Bay in Newport, RI The Auchincloss family estate had gardens designed by Frederick Law Olmsted, according to “A Life.” During the summer of 1961, when the Kennedys visited Hammersmith, the farm was dubbed “the summer White House” by the press, according to “Janet and Jackie.”</p><p> The White House installed phones in the main house and the Coast Guard inspected all boats and ships sailing past, the book said. After the oil crisis of the 1970s, Jackie&#39;s mother, Janet Auchincloss, sold the main house and about 54 acres for about $825,000 and the property was turned into a museum, the book said.</p><p> When plans to rezone the property and build condos emerged in the 1990s, William F. Farley, a Rhode Island native and former CEO of Fruit of the Loom, swooped in and paid $6.675 million in 1997, records show. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818413?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Jackie and John Kennedy&#39;s 1953 wedding reception took place at Hammersmith Farm, an Auchincloss-owned estate in Newport, RI</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Sygma/Getty Images </p></figcaption></figure></div><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818410?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> The Kennedys, pictured in 1962, had an office at Hammersmith.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Sygma/Getty Images</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> “My motivation was really simple,” he said. “It was to make sure it wouldn&#39;t get developed and it would remain part of American history.” Farley kept it as a museum, and sold it a few years later to Kiernan on the condition that Hammersmith would never be developed commercially. Kiernan paid just over $8 million, records show.</p><p> Kiernan said there was work to be done. “No one had lived here for a quarter-century,” he said. The Kiernans reinforced the structure with steel and wood beams, replaced the roof and redid the plumbing and electrical. They removed parking lots and restored farmland, and today Hammersmith is a working farm with horses, llamas and other animals; an old tea house has been repurposed as an aviary for peacocks, Kiernan said.</p><p> Kiernan said the Auchincloss family was “incredibly gracious” and gave him a portrait of Kennedy that is hanging in his office—which he was told Kennedy also used. The Kiernans, who purchased some of the home&#39;s original furniture at auction, have since held reunions at Hammersmith, he said. Kiernan said when he was working on Wall Street, the farm was like a “tonic” that would calm him. Two of his daughters have gotten married there, and the family feels a sense of responsibility for it. “We&#39;re trustees of it more than anything,” he said. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          smallrule
"><div class="wsj-article-page-rule"></div></div><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bleed
"><img width="600" height="1184" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/c35c58ed-3b19-46c9-a634-d14f37262157-fallback_app.jpg" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p> About three years after getting married, Jackie and John Kennedy bought a house in Hyannis Port that became part of the famous Kennedy compound. The couple paid $45,948 for the shingled house, located next to homes owned by John Kennedy&#39;s parents, Rose and Joe Kennedy, and his brother Robert F. Kennedy&#39;s home, records show. Built around 1925, Jackie and John Kennedy&#39;s house has about 4,484 square feet of interior space and sits on about 0.81 acres, according to the Barnstable County assessor. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          inline
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/3d2181e5-f058-4467-aecf-86900af4d845.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p> Spanning about 6 acres of waterfront, the compound was a base for Kennedy&#39;s presidential campaign. After the 1960 election, “the grass in front of Jack&#39;s deck became the temporary stage for twice-daily press conferences for the next couple of weeks,” according to Kate Storey&#39;s book “White House By the Sea: A Century of the Kennedys at Hyannis Port.” It remained a summer White House and presidential retreat until Kennedy&#39;s assassination in 1963, according to the National Park Service.</p><p> In 2004, Jackie&#39;s daughter, Caroline Kennedy, and son-in-law, Edwin Schlossberg, sold the house for $3 million to a Kennedy family trust, records show.  It is currently used as a summer residence by Ted Kennedy Jr. and his wife, Katherine “Kiki” Kennedy, who remodeled the house and donated the original windows, cabinets and shingles to the John F. Kennedy Hyannis Museum, according to Wendy Northcross, the museum&#39;s executive director. The museum allowed local artists to repurpose the materials into artifacts and other works of art. <strong>&nbsp;</strong> The house is currently worth around $4.5 million, according to Zillow&#39;s “Zestimate.” In 2012, Rose and Joe Kennedy&#39;s home—known as the Big House—was donated to the Edward M. Kennedy Institute for the US Senate to be preserved. “This house was my family&#39;s epicenter,” Ted Kennedy Jr. said at the time. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          smallrule
"><div class="wsj-article-page-rule"></div></div><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bleed
"><img width="600" height="1184" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/353f6970-acc1-491f-bed2-2a6632e698b3-fallback_app.jpg" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p> In 1957, before Kennedy&#39;s run for president, he and the future first lady bought their first house together, a red brick Federal-style building on N Street in Georgetown. “Kennedy paid $82,000 for it, and Jackie&#39;s remodeling cost another $18,000,” according to “A Life.” She filled the house with Louis XV armchairs and porcelains, Louis XVI dining chairs and an antique carpet. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          smallrule
"><div class="wsj-article-page-rule"></div></div><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bleed
"><img width="600" height="1184" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/6df2da95-261d-4182-8d6b-21e5eb6afd0b-fallback_app.jpg" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p> Following Kennedy&#39;s assassination in 1963, Jackie returned to Georgetown, where she bought a 1790s house that is currently listed on the National Register of Historic Places.</p><p> She paid about $175,000 for it, but moved to New York about a year later to escape the barrage of tourists that gathered outside, according to “A Life.” Yolande Betbeze Fox, a onetime Miss America, bought the house in 1976, records show. Construction entrepreneur David W. Hudgens purchased it for $5.25 million in 2017. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          edgetoedge
"><iframe width="300" height="300" src="https://graphics.wsj.com/dynamic-inset-iframer/?url=https://asset.wsj.net/wsjnewsgraphics/projects/narrator/86ad8303-f95c-4b8d-a0cf-faab53debfc2.json" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></iframe></div><p> Before buying Fox&#39;s house, Hudgens purchased two adjacent properties for $1.2 million and $1.625 million, records show. Once he owned the trio, he tapped architect Dale Overmyer to combine the properties into a mansion that is more than 15,300 square feet and has 13 bedrooms.</p><p> Overmyer said Hudgens had a passage built underneath the homes to connect them. Certain features of the former Kennedy home remain, including a wood-paneled library and dining room with gold leaf ceiling. The fireplaces—saved from a dumpster by Overmyer—are also original.</p><p> Following Hudgens&#39;s death in 2022, the assemblage of houses came on the market for $26.5 million this year. It is currently priced at $19.5 million, according to Zillow. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          smallrule
"><div class="wsj-article-page-rule"></div></div><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bleed
"><img width="600" height="1184" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/d9e069f1-5b2f-4564-92c0-54714ba10634-fallback_app.jpg" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p> Leaving Washington after Kennedy&#39;s death, Jackie purchased a 14-room apartment at 1040 Fifth Avenue, overlooking Central Park and the Metropolitan Museum of Art. “The arrangements for the apartment at 1040 Fifth were made so quietly that her name did not appear on the contract,” according to “Janet and Jackie,” which said she paid roughly $200,000 for the apartment, which spans the entire 15th floor. Jackie furnished the apartment with antique furniture and art, and lived there until her death in 1994, the book said.</p><p> The following year, the late billionaire David Koch purchased the apartment for $9.2 million, according to C. David Heymann&#39;s book “American Legacy: The Story of John and Caroline Kennedy,” published in 2008. “Mrs. Onassis was very conservative financially, and she didn&#39;t spend much on it,” Koch later told the Observer. “We gutted the apartment and redid everything.” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="488" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818401?width=700&amp;height=488" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Jackie, on Fifth Avenue in 1964, moved to New York to avoid publicity in Washington, DC</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：美联社</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>In 2006, Koch sold the apartment for $30 million to hedge funder Glenn Dubin and his wife, Eva Dubin, records show.</p><p> Although luxury buyers have more options than ever, including new condominiums, 1040 Fifth is still considered one of the city&#39;s best buildings, said Deborah Grubman of the Corcoran Group, who was involved in the 2006 sale. She said Jackie&#39;s celebrity status bolstered sales prices after she died—“She had some fake pearls that went for crazy numbers also,” Grubman said—but the building&#39;s attributes stand on their own. “Nobody did an apartment better than they did in those days,” she said. “The view is still something that&#39;s hard to duplicate.” </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          smallrule
"><div class="wsj-article-page-rule"></div></div><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bleed
"><img width="600" height="1380" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/6d3a48b2-8040-4709-941e-f2a338e85920-fallback_app.jpg" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p> In 1978, Jackie bought over 300 acres of land on the tip of Martha&#39;s Vineyard where she built a secluded summer residence known as Red Gate Farm. </p><div class="media-object scope-
          wrap
"><figure class="media-object-image img-wrap"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="639" height="959" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818424?width=639&amp;height=959" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> Jackie purchased more than 300 acres on Martha&#39;s Vineyard where she built a summer retreat.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Brooks Kraft/Sygma/Getty Images</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> After paying just over $1 million for the land, Jackie tapped architect Hugh Newell Jacobsen to design the shingled Cape Cod saltbox-style main house and a two-story guesthouse, which cost about $3.1 million and was completed in 1981, according to “A Life.” Philanthropist and horticulturist Rachel “Bunny” Mellon, who designed the White House Rose Garden when Jackie was first lady, designed the landscapes.</p><p> Over the years, Jackie hosted President Bill Clinton and others at the home, but she also clashed with a group of the Wampanoag Native Americans, who claimed the right to access a beachfront area on her property. (She settled the dispute in 1990.)</p><p> After Jackie&#39;s death, her daughter, Caroline Kennedy, and son-in-law, Edwin Schlossberg, enlisted Deborah Berke, dean of the Yale School of Architecture, to head up a multimillion-dollar renovation of the property, which also includes a pool, a tennis court and a treehouse Jackie built for her grandchildren. Caroline Kennedy listed it for sale in 2019, asking $65 million. At the time, she said in a statement that her three children had grown and it was time for the family to “spread its wings.” </p><div class="media-object scope-
          edgetoedge
"><figure class="media-object-image img-edgetoedge"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="1260" height="840" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-818505?width=1260&amp;height=840" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> She paid about $1 million for the land and built a house that was completed in 1981.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Christie&#39;s International Real Estate</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> In 2020 and 2021, however, two conservation groups—the Martha&#39;s Vineyard Land Bank Commission and Sheriff&#39;s Meadow Foundation—bought the land in separate transactions totaling $37 million, the groups said. The family retained roughly 60 acres, including the residence.</p><p> “Many of these land conservation efforts take decades to achieve,” said Adam Moore, president of Sheriff&#39;s Meadow Foundation, who described the deal as “the pinnacle of my career in conservation.” The groups are currently seeking permits to open the property, now known as Squibnocket Pond Reservation, to the public. </p><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          smallrule
"><div class="wsj-article-page-rule"></div></div><div class="media-object scope-web|mobileapps
          bleed
"><img width="600" height="1184" src="https://s.wsj.net/public/resources/images/b46c7859-e02b-424e-bc15-d0b3c7548cc6-fallback_app.jpg" alt="不明确的" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><p> During the last decades of her life, Jackie retreated to a country home in New Jersey where she could ride horses. Located in Bernardsville, NJ, the property cost about $200,000 in 1974 and included a “two-story frame house on 10 acres of lush hunt country,” according to “A Life.” Jackie painted the outside yellow with white trim, the book said. “Inside, she furnished it with comfortable, chintz-covered country pieces.”</p><p> After she died, then-Sen. Bill Bradley of New Jersey said Jackie adopted Bernardsville “in pursuit of that elusive privacy” that she sought for much of her life. “There she indulged in her favorite pastime of horseback riding,” he said, in a memorial tribute shared with Congress.</p><p> In 1997, Caroline Kennedy and her brother, John F. Kennedy Jr., sold the property to their mother&#39;s former neighbor, Marjorie “Peggy” McDonnell Walsh for $1.475 million, records show.</p><p> “We tore down the house and built a new one,” Walsh said, declining to share details about the new house. “It doesn&#39;t matter,” she said. “The much more important thing is we both love the property. It&#39;s a private valley. It&#39;s beautiful.”</p><p> Write to EB Solomont at <a href="mailto:eb.solomont@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">eb.solomont@wsj.com</a></p><div class="media-object scope-web
          inline
"><div class="media-object-rich-text"><h4>分享你的意见</h4><p><em>Which of Jackie Kennedy&#39;s properties do you think is the most iconic?加入下面的对话。</em></p></div></div></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 21 Jul 2023 04:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/jackie-os-collection-of-homes-was-as-iconic-as-it-gets-2500daf4</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/jackie-os-collection-of-homes-was-as-iconic-as-it-gets-2500daf4<author><![CDATA[E.B. Solomont]]></author><category>世家大厦</category><category>photo-research</category><category>建筑施工</category><category>住宅建筑施工</category><category>Construction</category><category>房地产/建筑</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>家居与园艺</category><category>home &amp; garden</category><category>建筑施工</category><category>住宅建筑施工</category><category>建造</category><category>房地产</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[U.S. Ambassador to China Hacked in China-Linked Spying Operation]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div>间谍活动还损害了负责东亚事务的国务院官员的安全<!-- data-module-name="article.app/lib/module/wsj/breadcrumbs" --><main id="main" role="main"><div class="wsj-article-headline-wrap crawler"></div><div class="articleLead" itemprop="articleLead" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001071218"><div class="is-lead-inset"><div class="media-object scope-
          header
"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-821061?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">美国驻华大使尼古拉斯·伯恩斯本月早些时候在美国驻北京大使馆举行的气候金融圆桌讨论会上发表讲话。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：mark schiefelbein/pool/Shutterstock </p></figcaption></figure></div></div></div><div class="articleBody" data-sbid="WP-WSJ-0001071218"><div class="clearfix bylineWrap"><div class="byline">作者： <span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/dustin-volz" itemprop="url" rel="author">达斯汀·沃尔兹 (Dustin Volz)</a></span>和<span class="author" itemprop="name"><a href="https://www.wsj.com/news/author/warren-p-strobel" itemprop="url" rel="author">沃伦·P·史特博 (Warren P. Strobel)</a></span></div><time class="timestamp article__timestamp flexbox__flex--1">更新于 2023 年 7 月 20 日下午 6:48（美国东部时间） </time></div><div subscriptions-actions="" subscriptions-display="NOT data.noSharing"><div class="share-bar"><amp-social-share type="system" width="72" height="24" data-param-url="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-ambassador-to-china-hacked-in-china-linked-spying-operation-f03de3e4"></amp-social-share></div></div><section subscriptions-section="content"><p>据知情人士透露，与北京有关的黑客访问了美国驻华大使尼古拉斯·伯恩斯(Nicholas Burns)的电子邮件帐户，此次攻击据信已泄露了至少<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/microsoft-email-hack-shows-greater-sophistication-skill-of-chinas-cyberspies-7f7cff67?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">数十万封美国政府的个人电子邮件</a>。</p><p>知情人士称，负责东亚事务的助理国务卿丹尼尔·克里滕布林克(Daniel Kritenbrink)也在网络间谍攻击中遭到黑客攻击。其中一位知情人士称，这两名外交官据信是上周披露的涉嫌间谍活动的两名国务院最高官员。</p><p>该活动的轮廓尚不完全清楚。尽管仅限于非机密电子邮件，但伯恩斯和克里滕布林克的收件箱可能让黑客能够深入了解美国拜登政府高级官员最近一系列访华的计划，以及在近几个月来一再受到挑战的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-and-china-look-to-repair-ties-again-9e200b10?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">微妙外交时期</a>美国对其竞争对手政策的内部对话。</p><p>伯恩斯和克里滕布林克是新闻报道中第二位和第三位被确认电子邮件遭到黑客攻击的拜登政府高级官员。美国官员表示，商务部长吉娜·雷蒙多的电子邮件帐户<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinese-hackers-spied-on-state-department-13a09f03?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">也因此次泄露</a>而受到损害。</p><p>一位知情人士表示，国务卿安东尼·布林肯的电子邮件帐户及其高级顾问圈子的电子邮件帐户似乎并未在此次黑客攻击中直接渗透。相反，黑客似乎把重点放在了少数负责管理美中关系的高级官员身上。</p><p>知情人士称，对个人电子邮件访问量的估计是粗略的，并且可能会增加。</p><p>美国国务院发言人表示：“出于安全原因，我们目前不会分享有关此次网络安全事件的性质和范围的更多信息。” “该部门持续监控并响应我们网络上值得关注的活动。我们的调查正在进行中，目前无法提供更多细节。”</p><p>白宫国家安全委员会拒绝置评。</p><p>一个月前，克里滕布林克陪同布林肯访华，克里滕布林克、伯恩斯和布林肯都出席了<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/xi-jinping-to-meet-blinken-monday-as-u-s-china-resume-high-level-engagement-c898f541?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">与中国高级官员和中国领导人习近平的会晤</a>。在北京举行高层会谈之前，克里滕布林克率领较低级别官员进行了一次访问<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/u-s-and-china-prepare-for-possible-blinken-visit-to-beijing-2173d40d?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">，以奠定基础</a>。 </p><div class="media-object scope-
          inline
"><figure class="media-object-image img-inline"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="700" height="466" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-821065?width=700&amp;height=466" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent">负责东亚事务的助理国务卿丹尼尔·克里滕布林克(Daniel Kritenbrink)在网络间谍攻击中遭到黑客攻击。</p><p class="imageCredit">照片：韩联社/ZUMA Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p>国务院领导拜登政府努力加强与中国的沟通，并在气候变化和合成阿片类药物贸易等特定领域取得进展。官员们表示<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/taiwan-elections-a-big-topic-during-blinkens-talks-in-china-afaa6def?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">，在台湾、间谍和其他问题上根深蒂固的分歧</a>导致两国关系恶化，而美国对中国的广泛政治担忧阻止了这一趋势的逆转。</p><p>据该公司称，最近的黑客攻击是利用了<a href="https://www.wsj.com/market-data/quotes/MSFT" class="">微软</a><span class="company-name-type">云</span>计算环境中的一个缺陷，该缺陷已得到修复，全球有超过两打组织受到影响。美国一位高级网络安全官员上周表示，美国只有不到 10 个组织受到攻击，而且每个组织似乎都拥有少量被黑客直接访问的个人电子邮件帐户。目前尚不清楚州和商务部以外的任何联邦机构是否成为攻击目标。</p><p>微软尚未公开披露此次泄露事件是如何开始的，并表示正在继续调查该事件。</p><p>美国官员将这次攻击描述为外科手术性质的攻击——针对少数专门选择的高价值受害者——并试图淡化其总体影响，将其比作敌对国家之间不断发生的常规数字间谍活动。</p><p>但安全专家和前情报官员表示，这次袭击似乎异乎寻常地隐蔽且令人印象深刻，并指出，此次袭击发生在美国和中国之间的外交关系有所加强之际，此前几个月， <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/ukraine-war-counteroffensive-frontlines-russia-add3e4e4?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">乌克兰战争</a>、美国发现并击落了所谓的<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/chinese-spy-balloon-over-the-u-s-what-to-know-11675385792?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">中国监视气球</a>，以及<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/beijing-plans-a-new-training-facility-in-cuba-raising-prospect-of-chinese-troops-on-americas-doorstep-e17fd5d1" target="_blank" class="icon none">中国与古巴加强情报合作</a>的消息曝光，两国关系急剧恶化。</p><p>周四在阿斯彭安全论坛上被问及此次黑客攻击时，微软总裁布拉德·史密斯表示，这次网络攻击反映出黑客“日益成熟”，其目的是“从非机密电子邮件系统中提取信息”。</p><p>国家安全局网络安全主管罗布·乔伊斯（Rob Joyce）出现在史密斯旁边，他补充说，这次黑客攻击相当于美国政府一直面临的“相当传统的威胁”。</p><p> “这是中国在从事间谍活动，”乔伊斯说。 “这就是民族国家所做的事情。我们需要防御它，我们需要反击它，但这就是发生的事情。”</p><p>美国尚未正式将此次黑客攻击归咎于中国，但拜登政府高级官员表示，他们没有理由怀疑微软将其与中国黑客组织联系起来的评估。中国否认了这些指控，并指责美国在世界各地从事猖獗的网络间谍活动。</p><p>美国国务院的网络安全专家最先发现了间谍活动。微软表示，黑客攻击始于 5 月份，但直到 6 月中旬才被发现，这一日期与布林肯访华的时间非常吻合，布林肯是五年来首位访问北京的美国国务卿。</p><p class="articleTagLine"> ——威廉·莫尔丁对本文做出了贡献。</p><p>写信给达斯汀·沃尔兹 ( <a href="mailto:dustin.volz@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">dustin.volz@wsj.com)</a>和沃伦·P·史特博 (Warren P. Strobel) ( <a href="mailto:Warren.Strobel@wsj.com" target="_blank" class="icon ">Warren.Strobel@wsj.com)</a></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Thu, 20 Jul 2023 22:48:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/us-ambassador-to-china-hacked-in-china-linked-spying-operation-f03de3e4</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/us-ambassador-to-china-hacked-in-china-linked-spying-operation-f03de3e4<author><![CDATA[Dustin VolzWarren P. Strobel]]></author><category>专有的</category><category>政治/一般新闻</category><category>国家/公共安全</category><category>犯罪/法律诉讼</category><category>隐私问题/信息安全</category><category>国际关系</category><category>网络犯罪/黑客攻击</category><category>政治/国际关系</category><category>国内政治</category><category>数据安全漏洞</category><category>Espionage</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法激活过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category><category>SYND</category><category>华尔街日报-PRO-WSJ.com</category><category>丹尼尔·克里滕布林克</category><category>尼古拉斯·伯恩斯</category><category>政治的</category><category>一般新闻</category><category>国家的</category><category>公安</category><category>犯罪</category><category>合法举动</category><category>隐私问题</category><category>信息安全</category><category>国际关系</category><category>网络犯罪</category><category>黑客攻击</category><category>政治</category><category>国内政治</category><category>数据安全漏洞</category><category>espionage</category><category>内容类型</category><category>法蒂瓦过滤器</category><category>C&amp;E 行政新闻过滤器</category></item></channel></rss>